text1_091cn:
女武神-级是标准驱逐舰规模的人员运输舰，其充足的内部空间足以单次运载两个连的陆战队员。就其规模而言，由于较大的船体以及脆弱的内部构造，导致女武神-级也只能在近距离内依靠最基本的防御火力，来勉强抵御战机和导弹。

其配备的地面支援武器能在大气中或着陆时为友军提供火力支援，因此女武神-级通常被应用于未开化世界的袭击行动中，扮演着快速部署重型陆战队员的角色。

因拥有对地面直接投放大量部队的能力，促使{霸主}的官僚们签署了一份'限购令'以禁止出售给未授权的第三方，然而这一限购消息在生效前，就已通过大量渠道泄露到公众世界中，也使某些目光短浅的投机者们似乎看到了所谓的未来商机。然而因生产过剩与功能有限等因素，不仅让这些投机者们血本无归，且在供大于求的情况下，显然获得一艘女武神-级要比{霸主}这条禁令在家喻户晓之前更为简单。

text2:
塔尔苏斯-级如此家喻户晓的原因，大概因为它是星域中最易组装、最耐用的货舰。

其可靠性的秘密在于：人之领}设计师最初就是把它设计成一种用于执行危险运输任务的货舰，目的大概是为了保障边境驻军和前线舰队的后勤补给，以平息在遥远战场上不断出现的暴动。

因舱壁结构密度与装甲等级是其他民用舰所无法比拟的，所以该舰经常被委托执行重要的运输工作,当然每次都有护卫队的随航，因为它们才是保护船员和货物安全的重要保障。

虽然仅配有最小级别且收效甚微的点防御武器，因此只有在极少数情况下，塔尔苏斯-级才会进行些战斗型船体和护甲提升的改造，尽管这会提高后勤维护难度，但之后广为流传的秃鹰-级改装方案却依旧让这艘货舰名声大噪。这种通过彻底拆除塔尔苏斯-级右侧货物架，却依旧保留了原民用级货舰温顺气质的全新航母，对那些粗心大意的敌人来说绝对是个巨大的惊喜。
text1_095:
Tarsus-class ships are well known as perhaps the most flexible and durable freighters in the Sector. 

The secret to their reliability is that they were intended by Domain designers as hazard duty ships, presumably to supply frontiers and those front line fleets send to quash the ever-present rumbling of insurrection on the far reaches of the Domain.

Almost unmatched among civilian ships in bulkhead structural density and armor rating, Tarsus-class freighters are entrusted with important hauls and usually travel in convoys, a further buttress to the safety they afford to their crew and cargo.

Minimal weapon mounts permit the ship to mount a nominal PD weapons package. Rarely, Tarsus-class ships are outfitted with combat oriented hull or armor boosting modifications, which make them more difficult to maintain.

text1_091cn:
塔尔苏斯-级如此家喻户晓的原因，大概因为它是星域中最易组装、最耐用的货舰。

其可靠性的秘密在于：人之领}设计师最初就是把它设计成一种用于执行危险运输任务的货舰，目的大概是为了保障边境驻军和前线舰队的后勤补给，以平息在遥远战场上不断出现的暴动。

因舱壁结构密度与装甲等级是其他民用舰所无法比拟的，所以该舰经常被委托执行重要的运输工作,当然每次都有护卫队的随航，因为它们才是保护船员和货物安全的重要保障。

虽然仅配有最小级别且收效甚微的点防御武器，因此只有在极少数情况下，塔尔苏斯-级才会进行些战斗型船体和护甲提升的改造，尽管这会提高后勤维护难度，但之后广为流传的秃鹰-级改装方案却依旧让这艘货舰名声大噪。这种通过彻底拆除塔尔苏斯-级右侧货物架，却依旧保留了原民用级货舰温顺气质的全新航母，对那些粗心大意的敌人来说绝对是个巨大的惊喜。

text2:
经常出没于商队或走私者舰队当中，除了执行运输任务，内置的飞行甲板也能帮助加强防御。

显然双子座-级高度模块化的设计理念，允许它能在战斗内外胜任多种角色。因整个货舱围绕着快速卸载机制而设计，这使该舰能够快速对接港口平台、迅速分离全部货物组、并在几分钟内交给另一艘双子座-级重复这一卸货过程。由于其小型飞行甲板起初是用于维修进行危险采矿作业的探矿无人机而设立的，但随着影响力上升，促使生产商运用现代化工艺扩展了飞行甲板，以支持标准战机的停靠。除此之外，凭借所配备的几处中型武器槽也使得双子座-级成为一种优秀的远程支援火力平台。

尽管它的蓝图令人印象深刻，但由于星域中缺乏足够兼容于双子座-级的集装箱，这便让快速卸载机制得不到合理应用。且过去备受推崇的模块化框架也因太易磨损，使保养比制造更加昂贵。尽管如此，如果将成本忽略不计，依靠不错的整体框架、体面的飞行甲板、灵活的幅能核心、良好的护盾系统，那么双子座-级很可能成为通用运输舰中的首选。
text1_095:
A common freighter, found in convoys or alone, used to haul all manner of goods across the Sector. Has a single fighter bay to bolster defenses.

The design of the Gemini-class freighter is highly modular, enabling the ship to serve in a variety of roles in and out of combat. The entire cargo container is designed around a quick release mechanism which enables the main hull of the ship to quickly call to port, detach its full cargo section, and swap it for another Gemini-type container in the span of minutes. In addition, multiple medium weapon mounts make the Gemini a viable long-range fire support platform. The flight deck is tiny, and was original envisioned for mining drone repair or hazardous mining operations. Modern use in the Sector extends flight deck facilities to all fighter types.

While impressive in a blueprint, the lack of empty, compatible Gemini-type containers in the Sector makes the actual usefulness of the quick-release mechanism negligible. The modularity, a great boon in times past is also more prone to wear and tear, and is thus more expensive to maintain - most working examples of the mechanisms have been welded solid. Nonetheless, a decent overall profile, the flight deck, a flexible power core and good shields make the Gemini a good choice for cargo hauling, if the cost can be weathered.

text2: 小巧且灵活的穿梭舱，旨在用于紧急情况下的人员转移或将某些高级官员快速送往目的地。
text1_095: A tiny, nimble personnel-transfer shuttle just sufficient to transport the senior bridge officers of any ship in the Sector.
text1_091: A tiny, nimble personnel-transfer shuttle just sufficient to transport the senior bridge officers of any ship in the Sector.
text1_091cn: 小巧且灵活的穿梭舱，旨在用于紧急情况下的人员转移或将某些高级官员快速送往目的地。

text2:
作为中型运输业的首选货舰，水牛-级充分体现了商队内所流行的调侃词：'装货并祈祷'。

由于整艘船基本是由大型引擎与货仓所组成，因此只保留有很小的船员舱并仅预留了一处小型武器槽,且侧向推进器仅能帮助该舰安全靠港而没有任何战术机动性，所以水牛-级通常不会单独执行运输任务。

因为引擎占据了该舰绝大数成本，所以尽管船体造价低廉，但仍处在一艘中型护卫舰的成本范围之内。因所有轨道船坞数据库里都有该舰的硬编码式蓝图，而这也就是该民用货舰几乎无处不在的根本原因。
text1_095:
The go-to choice for medium cargo hauling in the Sector, the Buffalo-class freighter exemplifies the "Load-n-Pray" principle prevalent in Sector shipping.

Sporting just a single small weapon emplacement, the hull of the ship is no more than a large engine with a tiny crew quarters section and cargo grapplers. A captain taking this ship out without a convoy rarely gets to make the same mistake twice. Incapable of anything resembling a combat maneuver, the lateral thrusters on Buffalo-class ships are designed to merely enable it to dock when (and if) it reaches its destination.

The ship engines are the greatest contributor to hull cost, which, while low, is still within the norms for a medium freighter. The greatest contributing factor to its ubiquity is the fact that the blueprint for this ship is usually hardcoded into every orbital shipyard's blueprint database.

由于整艘船基本是由大型引擎与货仓所组成，因此只保留有很小的船员舱并仅预留了一处小型武器槽,且侧向推进器仅能帮助该舰安全靠港而没有任何战术机动性，所以水牛-级通常不会单独执行运输任务。

因为引擎占据了该舰绝大数成本，所以尽管船体造价低廉，但仍处在一艘中型护卫舰的成本范围之内。因所有轨道船坞数据库里都有该舰的硬编码式蓝图，而这也就是该民用货舰几乎无处不在的根本原因。

text2:
压迫者-级在舰队中常作为执行护航任务的防御角色。尽管它的护盾性能令人失望，但依靠配备的良好装甲以及多个实弹武器挂载点，使这艘重型驱逐舰给人们留下了深刻的印象。

因其蓝图与攻势-级战列舰有许多相似之处，因此这也能从侧面印证了它们都是在{人之领}执行大规模军事扩张期间所设计出来的。如今该舰凭借充足武器与坚固舱壁，赢得了所有船员们的一致好评。

虽在同级别单挑中很难被轻易击败，但因航速较为缓慢，使其很少参与重要的大型战役。尽管如此，大批深受{霸主}战争学说影响的执法中队的手中，仍掌管不少由压迫者-级所组成的舰队并用以掩护沉重的攻势-级战列舰。因这两者的通用型配件能减轻不少后勤维护难度，而这正是那些{霸主}后勤官员们所希望看到的。
text1_095:
The Enforcer-class ships commonly serve in system or convoy defense roles. The design features good armor and multiple ballistic hardpoints, while shield performance is somewhat underwhelming. 

The blueprints of the ship call for many components similar to those found in the Onslaught-class battleships, suggesting that the designs were created during a similar period of military expansion in the Domain. The Enforcer-class features similar no-nonsense weapon system design choices, tough bulkheads, and is well regarded by its crews.

Tough to beat in a destroyer to destroyer fight, the Enforcer rarely takes part in larger battles due to the common view that its low speed makes it a liability. Nonetheless, Hegemony order of battle doctrines mandate an attached Enforcer squadron as a screen for Onslaught-class battleships. The logistical ease with which shared components can be used by both ship types is exactly the type of detail that excites Hegemony Logisticarum bureaucrats.

text2:
所有秃鹰-级轻型航母最初都是根据塔尔苏斯-级货舰船体改造而成。因二者转换过程涉及一些较为复杂的程序，所以需要适合的空间停靠设施与专业的模块设备才能完成改装。

星域中的一些人认为，在那个战乱纷飞的年代里，即使是{人之领}也不得不依靠这种类型的改造，运用他们全部的技术知识来使一艘民用舰发挥出最大的效用。而其他一些人则指出，这种改造的普遍性在当时还并不明确，也许之前就已经有很多秃鹰-级舰队已经遍布于星域当中了。可惜这两者说法均没有足够的证据，因为所有细节都在'大崩塌'中遗失了。

如今该舰之所以在星域中被广泛应用，是因这种改造方式对多数组织来说，是获取航母最简单的方法。尽管飞行甲板空间有限，但秃鹰-级凭借厚实的装甲、优异的结构强度和不错的武器配备(相对轻型航母)还是能出色地完成绝大数任务。
text1_095:
The Condor-class sees heavy service in the Sector as this carrier-converted freighter is, for many independent polities, the easiest way to procure fighter capability for their organization. Even with limited flight deck space, the Condor gets the job done, relying on its tough armor, excellent bulkhead strength, and a respectable (for a light carrier) weapons package.

This light carrier design is derived from Tarsus-class freighters modified by desperate scavengers and pirates. The conversion process was once an involved and complex affair requiring space dock facilities, but nowadays any hull-capable forge that will accept a stock Tarsus spec will, with the addition of a custom modchip, get you something just as good.

Some in the Sector argue that even the Domain, with all their technological know-how, relied on similar conversions to make more efficient use of a merchant fleet during times of escalated hostilities on the voluminous galactic frontier. Others point out that it is unclear how ubiquitous this approach was - there could have been fleets of Condors roaming Domain space, but there is scarce hard evidence one way or the other. Such data was all lost in the Collapse.

text2: 配有大型燃料罐，用于支持舰队燃料补给的中型燃料输送舰。在{霸主}补给舰队中任何被分配到辉腾-级的船员都被视为是一种惩罚，因为这种脆弱且毫无反抗力的舰船一旦被卷入战斗当中，其存活概率一般都非常之低。
text1_095: A medium tanker with enough fuel capacity to support a larger fleet. Tanker duty is often considered punitive in the Hegemony - there's little opportunity for distinction, and less chance of survival should direct contact with the enemy occur.
text1_091: A medium tanker with enough fuel capacity to support a larger fleet. Tanker duty is often considered punitive in the Hegemony - there's little opportunity for distinction, and less chance of survival should direct contact with the enemy occur.

text2: 旨在用于协助组装大型舰船和固定轨道的安装作业,或使用平台上的龙门架和操纵器来帮助打捞废弃船体，并从残骸和碎片中回收可用物资。因本身没有货舱与燃料罐,所以需要充足的后勤来保证其正常运作。随着打捞难度的提升，可能需要更多的维修平台来协同作业。
text1_095: Originally designed to assist in assembling large ships and orbital installations, the salvage rig's gantry and manipulators are used to assist in recovering derelict hulks and scavenging useful material from wreckage and debris fields. The rig itself has no cargo or fuel capacity and requires ample supply to maintain. Increases non-combat salvage gained, with more difficult operations being able to make use of more rigs.

text2: 容量巨大的燃料输送舰，用于在不同星系之间运输战略级的燃料量。不像它的小兄弟，该舰配备了合理的点防御武器，以保护那些宝贵且不稳定的货物。
text1_095: A tanker of vast capacity used to shift strategic quantities of fuel between worlds. Unlike its smaller cousins, the Prometheus features a reasonable defensive arsenal to protect its valuable and volatile cargo.
text1_091: A tanker of vast capacity used to shift strategic quantities of fuel between worlds. Unlike its smaller cousins, the Prometheus features a reasonable defensive arsenal to protect its valuable and volatile cargo.

text2:
An oddity among ships, the Monitor is the result of the line of thought that “sometimes the best defense is indeed the best defense”. Features turret mounts angled to provide wide arcs and a unique “flux shunt” modification to its power systems specially constructed to relieve flux generated by shields. Indeed, the Monitor makes up for a lack of maneuverability and firepower with the ability to withstand prolonged bombardment from enemy ordnance.

Though its experimental nature is perhaps a sign of the innovation that eras of turmoil seem to inspire, whether the Monitor’s radical defensive focus is a boon or pitfall remains contentious. Several dramatic failures in convoy protection patrols were explained by Ko Combine PR representatives to be the fault of improper tactics employed by convoy commanders. Ko Combine maintains that when positioned correctly in a combat situation and supported by strike-craft - as the anvil and hammer, respectively - simulations demonstrate that the Monitor significantly enhances convoy survivability against the average pirate attack. Prominent critics remain.

text1_091cn:
古怪的监视者-级很好地诠释了'有时防御才是最佳的进攻'这一理念。虽牺牲了机动性与火力，但凭借通用炮塔所提供的大弧度拦截区域，与磁通分流模块的先进耗散技术，使监视者-级能长时间承受与其吨位不成比例的猛烈打击。

虽然它的实验性质看起来像是引发这个动荡时代革新迹象的表现，但监视者-级激进化的防御侧重点依然是个富有争议性的话题。对于几次护航舰队在巡逻过程中被戏剧性的击败，{Ko}联合实业}公关代表的解释是：护航舰队的指挥官因战术失误而导致的，且他们认为,只要在战斗中保持正确的战斗队形，如铁砧与锤子的关系一样提供火力支援，监视者-级就能在应对一般海盗袭击中，有效提高护航舰队的生存几率。

text2:
能在载货量与战斗力之间达到合适平衡点而备受赞誉的武装商舰。地狱犬-级依靠体面的武器配备来防御大多数临时起意的抢劫行为。而这样做的好处是：与其它{人之领}标准民用货舰相比,它的保险费率更低。如今地狱犬-级凭借可靠船体、大型货舱、充足武器，活跃于小型贸易商队,或独立的走私舰队中。

在过去星门系统依旧运行的{人之领}统治时期，像地狱犬-级这样的武装商舰，仅只能在罕见的战区边缘或原始野蛮的星系腹地等{人之领}无敌舰队很少巡逻的地方才能见到。而那个年代里：船员的战斗训练、武器维护、和会导致质量/推力比损失的沉重装甲，都被视为没有必要的成本开销。但在这个充满危机和利益的新时代，地狱犬-级的可靠能力使它成为了商业贸易航线内的新兴力量。
text1_095:
The Cerberus is prized for providing a cost-effective balance between cargo capacity and enough combat power for its size to discourage casual piracy with the happy result of lowered insurance rates compared to standard Domain-era civilian grade freighters. The Cerberus is now widely considered to be a wise platform of operation for independent traders in the Sector. 

In times past, before the fall of the gate system when Domain authority reigned, combat-enabled freighters like the Cerberus found only niche use on the edges of the rare warzone or in especially uncivilized hinterlands of the galaxy where Domain Armada patrols were stretched thinly. The crew combat training, weapon maintenance, and mass/thrust ratio loss caused by heavier armour were viewed as causing unnecessary cost overhead. But this is a new age filled with both danger and profitable opportunities; the abilities of the Cerberus have given the hull a new life in the trade lanes.

text2:
The Heron provides the strategic and tactical mobility of a cruiser with potential firepower limited only by available strike-craft. It is the perfect accompaniment to the quick-moving and hard-hitting fleet of an admiral who knows when to take the initiative, hit quickly, and withdraw while enemy forces are still responding to the threat.

Historically the Heron represented a movement in Domain Armada strategy from a heavy capital ship doctrine based on overwhelming firepower toward a focus on strike craft and support cruisers that enable sufficient firepower to be quickly focused on weak points, a strategic shift that would reverse itself as a natural reaction against tradition from each successive generation of Armada officers. This process was occurring once more in the cycles immediately preceding the fall of the gate system and, in something of a coup for the so-called “Cruiser School”, the forward-thinking Altair Exotech won the Heron design contract over the traditional manufacturer of heavy Armada warships, Orion Shipyards. 

However the doctrinal shift embodied by the Heron was interrupted by the isolation of The Fall, and as such it is not often found in core Hegemony fleets (whose officers still cling to tradition). This hull has however found great popularity among the independent worlds, megacorporations, and mercenary forces of the Sector that tend to field leaner, faster fleets.

text1_091cn:
苍鹭-级能提供巡洋级别的战略与战术机动性，并能以火力全开的方式达到极限火力。对于喜欢采取'一击脱离'战术的舰队司令来说，拥有快速移动与高效打击能力的它无疑是最好的搭档。

历史上的苍鹭-级在{人之领}无敌舰队中的战略定位是多样的，不管是喜好依靠单艘重型主力舰压倒性火力来主导战场走向，或是善于利用多艘支援巡洋舰集中火力进行一点突破，任何想要从根本改变这些战略性质的决定性因素，都是由每一代愿意打破传统观念的无敌舰队总司令而决定的。而这艘充满多元化思想的轻型航母就出生于'大崩塌'的前一刻，一处被称为巡洋舰工程学院的地方，并由拥有前卫设计思想的'牵牛星科技'打败了传统重型战略军舰制造商'猎户座船坞'而赢得苍鹭-级的设计合同。

由于苍鹭-级所展现出的全新理念因'大崩塌'而遭到中断，导致如今即使在{霸主}核心舰队中(现任总司令依旧坚持传统)也很难看到该舰的身影。但它却依旧在联盟世界、超级企业、雇佣兵等这些崇尚精简、快速的地区中备受推崇。

text2:
根据巡洋舰工程学院所提出的全新设计理论，由{人之领}海军采购委员会公开招标,并交由代理商生产才让这艘具有战略用途(但战术单一)的廉价航母呈现在世人面前。赶牛人-级其无与伦比的战机整备性能都要归功于高效的甲板设计。是采取阿尔法打击在突袭中取得胜利,还是发挥威慑作用来遏制叛军的侵略行动？不管最终执行哪种决策，都是对那些下级军官们的一种考验。

为了从新兴海军生产商那恢复所失去的市场份额，老牌造船厂猎户座船坞最终以压倒性的优势获得了该舰的设计合同。但结果是：对于'飞行甲板'的独特设计，遭到了不少{人之领}官员的质疑,他们认为这种航母除了被后勤官员用于指挥外，不具备任何战斗能力。且随着海军部里一些下级军官对该舰的投诉量增多促使他们委托首都工程学院将改进意愿送到了委员会的手中。理由是：船体吨位与火力水平未达到预期标准，虽可通过搭载新型战斗机来改善，但依旧难以满足常规指挥任务需求，因此委员会考虑不超出预算的情况下，下令在舰首处安装导弹挂载点，并对驱动程序进行了一些细微的改动，以使其拥有基本的支援能力。
text1_095:
The Drover is a hull designed by the Cruiser-school-dominated Domain Naval Procurement Committee to provide a strategically versatile (though tactically limited) fighter platform with low logistical overhead. The fighter complement of the Drover is unmatched for its size. Command of a Drover is considered something of a test of character for junior officers: Will they use fearsome alpha-strike potential to seize victory in a sudden attack or hold back and use its threat to curtail aggressive moves by the opposition?

The contract for design of the Drover was won by Orion Shipyards, the traditional Armada ship-builder, in an effort to recover lost market share from the newer naval producers. The result was the 'flying landing strip' maligned by Domain officers as a command more fitting for a logistics bureaucrat than a fighting ship-captain. Complaints in the lower ranks were used by the old Capital-school faction to send the Drover back to committee, citing insufficient firepower for the ship class to meet standard guidelines (which did not account for the strike potential of new classes of fighters). Set up to take the fall for a massive overspend, the committee simply ordered an enormous number of simple missile hardpoints installed- this met the firepower requirements handily and allowed the Drover programme to proceed with only minor alteration.

text2:
常负责贫困边疆地区运输任务的可靠穿梭机。它的小船舱也经常被船员和乘客们客气地形容为'稳健的'家伙。尽管其简陋的设施需要经常定期维护，但它总能一如既往的将工作做好。

赫尔墨斯-级的武装虽然仅有'防止主动撞击'规格的水平，但它总能凭借三处满负荷运行的小炮塔来击落零星的来袭导弹，以用于从战斗区域中逃脱出来。但由于本身火力弱小且极其脆弱，因此只有一些疯狂绝望的船长才会在前线作战中使用到它。
text1_095:
The Hermes is a small, dependable cargo hauler often converted for transport duty among poor frontier worlds. Its crew and passenger facilities are charitably described as "robust" but it manages to get the job done with remarkable consistency despite the primitive maintenance facilities it frequents.

Factory-spec, the Hermes is armed only for "active collision avoidance", but its turret system is often upgraded to achieve nearly full albeit light point-defense coverage that can destroy the stray missile while escaping from active combat zones. This firepower is meagre compared to dedicated combat ships so only a mad or truly desperate captain would employ the Hermes in front line combat.

text2: 大型舰队的重要组成部分。公牛-级凭借驱动立场稳定器来让缓慢的大型舰船以较高的速度航行。但夸张的燃料消耗与高昂的维护成本，使绝大多数舰队很少携带超过两艘以上的公牛-级拖船。
text1_095: The Ox-class tug carries a drive field stabilizer that allows a fleet to reach a higher burn level. It's rare to see more than one or two of these in a fleet, however, due to prohibitive fuel consumption and high maintenance costs.
text1_091: The Ox-class tug carries a drive field stabilizer that allows a fleet to reach a higher burn level. It's rare to see more than one or two of these in a fleet, however, due to prohibitive fuel consumption and high maintenance costs.
text1_091cn: 大型舰队的重要组成部分。公牛-级凭借驱动立场稳定器来让缓慢的大型舰船以较高的速度航行。但夸张的燃料消耗与高昂的维护成本，使绝大多数舰队很少携带超过两艘以上的公牛-级拖船。

text2: 这艘轻型燃料输送舰其满载时的燃料储备，是小型作战部队或护航舰队所需燃料的两倍以上。
text1_095: A light tanker with enough fuel capacity to more than double the effective range of a small task force or convoy.
text1_091: A light tanker with enough fuel capacity to more than double the effective range of a small task force or convoy.
text1_091cn: 这艘轻型燃料输送舰其满载时的燃料储备，是小型作战部队或护航舰队所需燃料的两倍以上。

text2: 用于骚扰或支援的优秀护卫舰，虽哨兵-级能以不俗的速度与火力作为优势,对抗所有类型的敌人,但依旧非常容易淹没于大量战机联队的火力之下。
text1_095: An excellent harasser and support frigate, the Vigilance-class has oversized (for its class) energy and missile mounts. While it shines in a fleet setting, it can be easily overwhelmed by large numbers of smaller threats.
text1_091: An excellent harasser and support frigate, the Vigilance-class has oversized (for its class) energy and missile mounts. While it shines in a fleet setting, it can be easily overwhelmed by large numbers of smaller threats.
text1_091cn: 用于骚扰或支援的优秀护卫舰，虽哨兵-级能以不俗的速度与火力作为优势,对抗所有类型的敌人,但依旧非常容易淹没于大量战机联队的火力之下。

text2: 通常部署于星系警署部队或港务安保部队中。斗士-级通过牺牲机动性以换取令人印象深刻的火力、装甲以及驱逐级别的反应堆，而这种坚固耐用的设计也使它成为了为数不多拥有持久作战力的炮艇之一。
text1_095: Typically deployed to beef up system police forces and port authority security, the Brawler-class frigate is a robust design which trades mobility (and comfort) for impressive firepower, armor, and a destroyer-grade power generator.
text1_091: Typically deployed to beef up system police forces and port authority security, the Brawler-class frigate is a robust design which trades mobility (and comfort) for impressive firepower, armor, and a destroyer-grade power generator.

text2: 在扩张时代晚期设计出的先进且不对称的护卫舰。暴雨-级具备任何攻击护卫舰所拥有的精髓：高速、致命、难以摧毁。
text1_095: An asymmetric, advanced design from the late Expansion Epoch, the Tempest-class is the quintessential attack frigate - fast, deadly and difficult to destroy.
text1_091: An asymmetric, advanced design from the late Expansion Epoch, the Tempest-class is the quintessential attack frigate - fast, deadly and difficult to destroy.
text1_091cn: 在扩张时代晚期设计出的先进且不对称的护卫舰。暴雨-级具备任何攻击护卫舰所拥有的精髓：高速、致命、难以摧毁。

text2: 预兆-级很少被部署的原因在于所需的高昂成本，并不是所有势力与个人能随便承担的。但凭借其优异的护盾与独特的电磁脉冲发射器，使它成为了大型舰船的完美护卫。
text1_095: The Omen is rarely deployed due to the cost associated with maintaining such a technologically advanced ship. Its excellent shields and the EMP Emitter it carries make it a perfect escort for larger ships.
text1_091: The Omen is rarely deployed due to the cost associated with maintaining such a technologically advanced ship. Its excellent shields and the EMP Emitter it carries make it a perfect escort for larger ships.
text1_091cn: 预兆-级很少被部署的原因在于所需的高昂成本，并不是所有势力与个人能随便承担的。但凭借其优异的护盾与独特的电磁脉冲发射器，使它成为了大型舰船的完美护卫。

text2:
作为海盗与私人军队的最爱，除了其无处不在的蓝图，最重要的还是因无需太多配置的支持，就能让征伐-级拥有可观的实弹火力。

征伐-级的船长通常不善言谈，并钟爱用武器来与敌人深刻交流。除了善于粉碎敌舰来完成所有任务,并拒绝一切外交行为和隐秘手段。凭借轻型战机和护卫舰所难以抵御的爆发性实弹炮火，让征伐-级能更有效的执行绝大数快速袭击/保护中型商队的任务。如果这样还不能解决问题，就只能依靠携带一种令人讨厌的惊喜：两个导弹发射架所搭载的'终结者'类型的导弹，比如鱼叉{MRM。
text1_095:
A favorite of pirates and private armies due to the ubiquity of the blueprints and its non-demanding support profile, Lasher-class frigates pack a respectable amount of ballistic firepower.

Lasher captains are usually no-nonsense types who let their weapons do the talking, and pick through the debris of enemy ships as opposed to trying more diplomatic or covert means of getting the job done. More often than not, that job involves quickly and effectively striking at (or guarding) small or medium-sized trade convoys. The light fighter and frigate escorts usually found guarding such convoys are hardly a match for the hail of projectiles a Lasher can quickly unleash. If that does not get the job done, the Lasher has another nasty surprise in wait - two missile hardpoints, more often than not fitted with "finisher" types of missile, such as the Harpoon MRM.

text2:
大概是最小配有超光速引擎的舰船之一，通常用于在星系之间安全地运送重要的贵宾或信使。

虽然体积小巧，但足以安全舒适地运送{VIP}乘客。除非被迫卷入战斗当中，那一般很少能在战斗中看到它的身影，如果真不幸处于这样的境地，那么这时大多数乘客应该都会抱怨：为什么几乎所有的电力系统都用在了生命维持，以及为确保在漫长旅途中不会无聊的娱乐模块上。
text1_095:
One of the smallest ships in the Sector equipped with an on-board hyperdrive actuator, this class is typically used for safely transporting VIPs or couriers between star systems.

Although small, the Shuttle-class is outfitted for the comfort and security of its potential VIP passengers. It is rare to see one in combat; if a captain is unlucky enough to be in such a spot, one can quickly see why: most power systems on board are reserved for use by the life support, comfort and entertainment modules, installed to make sure that passengers do not get bored on long voyages.
text1_091:

text2:
A bleeding-edge advanced gunship built around a unique phase teleportation system. The finicky integrated prototype power grid is tricky and expensive to maintain but delivers excellent flux and shield performance. The Hyperion was built to 'punch up', using tactical positioning to pick its fights then engage with a relatively heavy weapon weapon loadout for its class, mounted at the expense of point defense capability.

Considered a 'hangar queen', the Hyperion is scorned by quartermasters yet prized by Tri-Tachyon fleet directors who admire the purity of the ambition which can be felt throughout its design and application.
text1_095:
A bleeding-edge advanced gunship built around a unique phase teleportation system. The finicky integrated prototype power grid is tricky and expensive to maintain but delivers excellent flux and shield performance. The Hyperion was built to 'punch up', using tactical positioning to pick its fights then engage with a relatively heavy weapon weapon loadout for its class, mounted at the expense of point defense capability.

Considered a 'hangar queen', the Hyperion is scorned by quartermasters yet prized by Tri-Tachyon fleet directors who admire the purity of the ambition which can be felt throughout its design and application.
text1_091:
A supremely advanced design, fragile but with a superb power generator and the ability to mount more ordnance than any other mainstream frigate. Extremely expensive for its size.

Due to the perfectly modular design of the hull, power couplings and weapon slots, modifications of this ship class are not taxing on in flux shunts, plasma relays or the power core. In short, hull modifications are extremely easy to complete. It is often the case that a Hyperion-class is finely tuned with a cornucopia of mutually boosting hull modifications that make it even deadlier that a variant that is simply bristling with weapons. Naturally, such special modifications are not for the engineering novice and the uninitiated may just blow their entire fortune on a concept that seems good on paper, but is in fact useless in the battlespace. That is why there are many engineers that shun this modification-heavy approach and opt for a more weapon focused platform.

The end results of either approach usually affirm the apprehensive attitude Sector stellators have toward this ship.
text1_091cn:
极其先进的设计。虽船体结构非常脆弱，但凭借一流的反应堆，和比其它主流护卫舰更强的火力，使其成为了星域中少数的'巨人猎手'，但对一艘护卫舰来说，不管是它的购买价格还是维护成本都太过昂贵了。

由于船体、能源耦合器和武器槽完美的模块化设计，使改造该舰并不会给它的幅能分流器、等离子继电器与幅能核心带来额外的压力。简而言之它的改造是极易完成的。通常情况下,经过精细而丰富的船体增强后的亥伯龙-级，要比单纯装满武器的改造要更为致命。当然，新手工程师是不会轻易进行这种特殊改造的，因为缺乏经验的人很可能因为纸上谈兵的构想而毁掉自己的前程，因此这就是为什么许多工程师避开船体改造，转而选择一种多武器搭载的方案。

不管怎样，这两种改造方案的最终结果肯定会让整个星域对这艘尖端护卫舰的恐惧心理跟进一步。

text2: 经久耐用但缺乏护盾发生器的古董护卫舰，它的主要用途一般被用于货物运输而不是战斗任务。但一名富有天赋或幸运的舰长依旧能靠猎犬-级来获得发家致富的机会。
text1_095: An old but durable hull class that lacks a shield generator, this frigate is sometimes used to ferry cargo instead of for combat duty. A lucky or gifted officer could make his fortune given the chance to captain one.
text1_091: An old but durable hull class that lacks a shield generator, this frigate is sometimes used to ferry cargo instead of for combat duty. A lucky or gifted officer could make his fortune given the chance to captain one.
text1_091cn: 经久耐用但缺乏护盾发生器的古董护卫舰，它的主要用途一般被用于货物运输而不是战斗任务。但一名富有天赋或幸运的舰长依旧能靠猎犬-级来获得发家致富的机会。

text2: 技术先进的护卫舰，依靠良好的机动性、优秀的护盾以及令人印象深刻的武器配置，使其足以用来对付远超该舰吨位的大型战舰。但同时也意味着仅配备标准护卫级幅能核心的野狼-级在交战中，要谨慎控制幅能水平，否则后果将是极其致命的。
text1_095: A technologically advanced frigate with an efficient shield generator and an impressive weapons package that allows it to punch far above its weight. These same characteristics mean its frigate-grade power core struggles to keep up, making careful flux management a priority.
text1_091: A technologically advanced frigate with an efficient shield generator and an impressive weapons package that allows it to punch far above its weight. These same characteristics mean its frigate-grade power core struggles to keep up, making careful flux management a priority.
text1_091cn: 技术先进的护卫舰，依靠良好的机动性、优秀的护盾以及令人印象深刻的武器配置，使其足以用来对付远超该舰吨位的大型战舰。但同时也意味着仅配备标准护卫级幅能核心的野狼-级在交战中，要谨慎控制幅能水平，否则后果将是极其致命的。

text2: 速度优异、装备精良且拥有很长的交战范围。雷霆-级的作用在于使航母能够在需要的位置上快速投放打击力量。由于不具备轰炸机那样的决定性火力与重型战斗机那样的可靠装甲，因此当被迫与全副武装的单一目标持续交战时，其缺点也会愈发明显。
text1_095: Extremely fast, well-armed, and with a long engagement range, the Thunder's strength lies in enabling a carrier to rapidly project force at the desired location. Not as damaging as a bomber or as tough as a heavy fighter, it will falter if forced into a prolonged engagement.
text1_091: Extremely fast, well-armed, and with a long engagement range, the Thunder's strength lies in enabling a carrier to rapidly project force at the desired location. Not as damaging as a bomber or as tough as a heavy fighter, it will falter if forced into a prolonged engagement.
text1_091cn: 速度优异、装备精良且拥有很长的交战范围。雷霆-级的作用在于使航母能够在需要的位置上快速投放打击力量。由于不具备轰炸机那样的决定性火力与重型战斗机那样的可靠装甲，因此当被迫与全副武装的单一目标持续交战时，其缺点也会愈发明显。

text2: 凭借充足的高爆武器与精湛的厚重装甲，使它足以威胁到大型舰船。尽管缺乏动能武器，但所携带的诱饵发射器可以充分吸引敌舰点防御武器的火力，并借此帮助自己和脆弱的盟友提高存活几率。
text1_095: Boasting superb armor with firepower to match, the Warthog is capable of trading blows with larger ships, but lacks shield-breaking weapons. A decoy flare launcher helps draw fire away from its more vulnerable allies.
text1_091: Boasting superb armor with firepower to match, the Warthog is capable of trading blows with larger ships, but lacks shield-breaking weapons. A decoy flare launcher helps draw fire away from its more vulnerable allies.
text1_091cn: 凭借充足的高爆武器与精湛的厚重装甲，使它足以威胁到大型舰船。尽管缺乏动能武器，但所携带的诱饵发射器可以充分吸引敌舰点防御武器的火力，并借此帮助自己和脆弱的盟友提高存活几率。

text2: 快速、致命、可靠。短剑-级凭借出色的生存能力以及充足火力，让它可以轻松消灭数倍于自身数量的脆弱战机。但当与难缠的重型战舰持续交战时，它就只能依靠诱饵发射器来为自己争取宝贵的时间。
text1_095: Fast, deadly and well-armored, the Gladius excels at improving both the firepower and survivability of interceptor groups. However, when facing durable opponents, the small number of craft in a wing begins to tell.
text1_091: Fast, deadly and well-armored, the Gladius excels at improving both the firepower and survivability of interceptor groups. However, when facing durable opponents, the small number of craft in a wing begins to tell.
text1_091cn: 快速、致命、可靠。短剑-级凭借出色的生存能力以及充足火力，让它可以轻松消灭数倍于自身数量的脆弱战机。但当与难缠的重型战舰持续交战时，它就只能依靠诱饵发射器来为自己争取宝贵的时间。

text2: 坚固的探矿无人机可以提供一定的防御火力与火力支援的作用，由于{AI}系统只设有'护航模式'，因此无法离开母舰进行远程作战。
text1_095: Sturdy and uncrewed, the Mining Pod can provide a bit of a distraction and a bit of fire support, and not much else. Incapable of operating away from the mothership.
text1_091: Sturdy and uncrewed, the Mining Pod can provide a bit of a distraction and a bit of fire support, and not much else. Incapable of operating away from the mothership.
text1_091cn: 坚固的探矿无人机可以提供一定的防御火力与火力支援的作用，由于{AI}系统只设有'护航模式'，因此无法离开母舰进行远程作战。

text2: 配备有护盾的高速轰炸机。善于利用动能导弹来远程压制敌舰护盾，并快速返回航母来重新装填，因此与其它传统轰炸机联合打击时，就能将长弓-级的优势发挥到最大。
text1_095: Fast and equipped with a shield generator, the Longbow's job is to deploy its kinetic Sabot missile from range and return to the carrier to rearm. Most effective when its shield-breaking kinetic damage is combined with that of heavier damage-dealers.
text1_091: Fast and equipped with a shield generator, the Longbow's job is to deploy its kinetic Sabot missile from range and return to the carrier to rearm. Most effective when its shield-breaking kinetic damage is combined with that of heavier damage-dealers.
text1_091cn: 配备有护盾的高速轰炸机。善于利用动能导弹来远程压制敌舰护盾，并快速返回航母来重新装填，因此与其它传统轰炸机联合打击时，就能将长弓-级的优势发挥到最大。

text2: 配备有一流护盾发生器并搭载有两架阿特罗波斯级鱼雷发射器的高效鱼雷轰炸机。尽管极具威胁，但较低的航速与苛刻的后勤限制了'三叉戟'的有效性。
text1_095: Equipped with dual Atropos-class torpedoes and a top-notch shield generator, the Trident is perhaps the most feared of all bombers. Its effectiveness is somewhat limited by its low top speed and demanding logistical profile.
text1_091: Equipped with dual Atropos-class torpedoes and a top-notch shield generator, the Trident is perhaps the most feared of all bombers. Its effectiveness is somewhat limited by its low top speed and demanding logistical profile.
text1_091cn: 配备有一流护盾发生器并搭载有两架阿特罗波斯级鱼雷发射器的高效鱼雷轰炸机。尽管极具威胁，但较低的航速与苛刻的后勤限制了'三叉戟'的有效性。

text2: 食人鱼-级通过推送大量无动力的标准炸弹，来迅速压制或摧毁缺乏防御火力的大型目标。尽管在理想情况下其威胁程度远超于其它同类型战机，但事实上这种脆弱的轰炸机连同所发射的标准炸弹，很容易被敌舰的防御火力所快速摧毁。
text1_095: The Piranha deploys unpowered conventional bombs en masse, relying on momentum to deliver the payloads. The maximum damage potential is extreme, but most targets can either avoid or shoot down many of the bombs.
text1_091: The Piranha deploys unpowered conventional bombs en masse, relying on momentum to deliver the payloads. The maximum damage potential is extreme, but most targets can either avoid or shoot down many of the bombs.
text1_091cn: 食人鱼-级通过推送大量无动力的标准炸弹，来迅速压制或摧毁缺乏防御火力的大型目标。尽管在理想情况下其威胁程度远超于其它同类型战机，但事实上这种脆弱的轰炸机连同所发射的标准炸弹，很容易被敌舰的防御火力所快速摧毁。

text2: 坚韧且敏捷的重型战斗机，阔剑-级善于利用诱饵发射器来使防御火力远离高价值目标，如轰炸机和它们所释放出的爆炸物。但因配备的轻机枪只能威胁到护盾，所以该战机无法单独处理摧毁目标的任务。
text1_095: Tough and agile, the Broadsword carries a decoy flare launcher that draws defensive fire away from high-value targets like bombers and their payloads. However, it can falter if faced with the need to deal the killing blow itself.
text1_091: Tough and agile, the Broadsword carries a decoy flare launcher that draws defensive fire away from high-value targets like bombers and their payloads. However, it can falter if faced with the need to deal the killing blow itself.
text1_091cn: 坚韧且敏捷的重型战斗机，阔剑-级善于利用诱饵发射器来使防御火力远离高价值目标，如轰炸机和它们所释放出的爆炸物。但因配备的轻机枪只能威胁到护盾，所以该战机无法单独处理摧毁目标的任务。

text2: 希腊剑-级凭借严密的远程防御火力，使其密接支援方面表现突出。虽然支持任何非母公司生产的航母，但由于需依赖大型舰船的定位与导航模块的辅助，所以意味着它无法远离母舰进行独立作战。
text1_095: Heavily shielded and armed with long range weapons, the Xyphos is highly effective in a close support role. Its reliance on targeting and navigation feeds from larger ships mean it's incapable of operating independently, though it is able to support ships other than its parent carrier.
text1_091: Heavily shielded and armed with long range weapons, the Xyphos is highly effective in a close support role. Its reliance on targeting and navigation feeds from larger ships mean it's incapable of operating independently, though it is able to support ships other than its parent carrier.
text1_091cn: 希腊剑-级凭借严密的远程防御火力，使其密接支援方面表现突出。虽然支持任何非母公司生产的航母，但由于需依赖大型舰船的定位与导航模块的辅助，所以意味着它无法远离母舰进行独立作战。

text2: 快速且灵活，黄蜂无人机依靠数量上的优势，利用毒刺-级感应空雷来快速瓦解敌方战机阵线。尽管缺乏护盾的保护导致在面对敌舰防御火力拦截时表现得尤为脆弱，但由于无需驾驶员，因此造成的任何损失都在可控范围之内。
text1_095: Fast and nimble, Wasp drones typically outnumber and easily swarm enemy fighter formations while their Stinger mines prevent stragglers from getting through. Faced with point-defense weaponry, their fragility begins to tell, but the lack of a pilot on board means losses are more easily absorbed.
text1_091: Fast and nimble, Wasp drones typically outnumber and easily swarm enemy fighter formations while their Stinger mines prevent stragglers from getting through. Faced with point-defense weaponry, their fragility begins to tell, but the lack of a pilot on board means losses are more easily absorbed.
text1_091cn: 快速且灵活，黄蜂无人机依靠数量上的优势，利用毒刺-级感应空雷来快速瓦解敌方战机阵线。尽管缺乏护盾的保护导致在面对敌舰防御火力拦截时表现得尤为脆弱，但由于无需驾驶员，因此造成的任何损失都在可控范围之内。

text2: 配有高度破坏性鱼雷的脆弱轰炸机，匕首-级依靠低效的前置护盾，来使自己尽可能坚持到最佳发射距离，而不至于被中途摧毁。然而，它们所发射的大型鱼雷弹幕依旧难以越过密集的防御火力，且自身也会被摆脱鱼雷困扰的点防御武器迅速抹杀。
text1_095: Armed with a highly damaging torpedo, the Dagger is fragile but equipped with a shield generator that usually enables it to get within launch range. However, even a large torpedo barrage is unlikely to get through concentrated point-defense fire without a distraction.
text1_091: Armed with a highly damaging torpedo, the Dagger is fragile but equipped with a shield generator that usually enables it to get within launch range. However, even a large torpedo barrage is unlikely to get through concentrated point-defense fire without a distraction.
text1_091cn: 配有高度破坏性鱼雷的脆弱轰炸机，匕首-级依靠低效的前置护盾，来使自己尽可能坚持到最佳发射距离，而不至于被中途摧毁。然而，它们所发射的大型鱼雷弹幕依旧难以越过密集的防御火力，且自身也会被摆脱鱼雷困扰的点防御武器迅速抹杀。

text2: 廉价、快速、拥有惊人火力的截击机，当大量部署时，就可以威胁到一些较大的战舰。但这样做就要承受损失大量飞行员的后果。
text1_095: Fast and cheap, the Talon sports surprising firepower and is capable of dispatching enemy fighters. It can also deal appreciable damage to larger ships when used en masse, though such use usually results in heavy pilot losses.
text1_091: Fast and cheap, the Talon sports surprising firepower and is capable of dispatching enemy fighters. It can also deal appreciable damage to larger ships when used en masse, though such use usually results in heavy pilot losses.
text1_091cn: 廉价、快速、拥有惊人火力的截击机，当大量部署时，就可以威胁到一些较大的战舰。但这样做就要承受损失大量飞行员的后果。

text2: 镰状剑-级善于利用精确且毁灭性的火箭弹幕来打击目标，尽管潜在破坏力略逊一筹，但它依旧要比其它轰炸机更加安全、可靠。
text1_095: The Khopesh can deliver an accurate and devastating rocket barrage to its target. Safer and more reliable in dealing its damage than other bombers, it also doesn't boast quite the same damage potential.
text1_091: The Khopesh can deliver an accurate and devastating rocket barrage to its target. Safer and more reliable in dealing its damage than other bombers, it also doesn't boast quite the same damage potential.
text1_091cn: 镰状剑-级善于利用精确且毁灭性的火箭弹幕来打击目标，尽管潜在破坏力略逊一筹，但它依旧要比其它轰炸机更加安全、可靠。

text2: 拥有低效护盾且机动性卓越的支援战斗机。善于利用{EMP}武器短暂瘫痪一些没有护盾的目标，但依旧无法造成任何实质性的损伤。
text1_095: Nimble and equipped with a low-grade shield generator, the Claw is primarily a support fighter. The EMP damage it deals is temporarily crippling to poorly-shielded targets, but it's incapable of dealing much permanent damage on its own.
text1_091: Nimble and equipped with a low-grade shield generator, the Claw is primarily a support fighter. The EMP damage it deals is temporarily crippling to poorly-shielded targets, but it's incapable of dealing much permanent damage on its own.
text1_091cn: 拥有低效护盾且机动性卓越的支援战斗机。善于利用{EMP}武器短暂瘫痪一些没有护盾的目标，但依旧无法造成任何实质性的损伤。

text2: 缓慢且脆弱，这种武装化的探矿无人机不仅能远离母舰执行任务，且利用数量优势，依旧可以威胁到一些落单的小型目标。
text1_095: Slow and not very sturdy, this combat-modified mining drone is nonetheless capable of keeping hostiles off its mothership for a time. Fielded in numbers, it can even present a credible threat to smaller combat ships.
text1_091: Slow and not very sturdy, this combat-modified mining drone is nonetheless capable of keeping hostiles off its mothership for a time. Fielded in numbers, it can even present a credible threat to smaller combat ships.
text1_091cn: 缓慢且脆弱，这种武装化的探矿无人机不仅能远离母舰执行任务，且利用数量优势，依旧可以威胁到一些落单的小型目标。

text2: 基于可怕的终结者核心目标分析仪而建造的点防无人机，它能让其在一瞬间准确无误地发现导弹与战机上的弱点，并予以致命打击。而关于核心内搭载的AI水平会在复杂战况下间歇性地超过所允许的德尔塔级的传言至今依旧未被证实。
text1_095: A point-defense drone built around the dreaded Terminator Core target analyzer, which finds transient weak points on missiles and fighters with unerring precision. Rumors about the core's AI intermittently exceeding the generally-allowed delta level during complex combat situations remain unproven.
text1_091: A point-defense drone built around the dreaded Terminator Core target analyzer, which finds transient weak points on missiles and fighters with unerring precision. Rumors about the core's AI intermittently exceeding the generally-allowed delta level during complex combat situations remain unproven.

text2:
创造于相位技术还是一种新兴科技的时代,且那时的隐形探测器还并非所有感应器的封装标准。尽管如今失去了突袭的优势，但仍不失为一种危险且灵活的武器平台。

虽然有大量因长期服役于该舰的船员出现不同程度的心理疾病，但{人之领}海军依旧未对其做出任何官方声明，并且所有相关资料也一并在'大崩塌'后遗失。
text1_095:
Designed when phase technology was generally unknown and phase detectors were not a standard of every sensor package, this cruiser has lost the advantage of surprise - but retains a dangerous and flexible weapons loadout. 

Certain unnerving psychological phenomena have been reported by sensitive crew members after enduring many rapid phase-shifts in combat conditions. Domain Navy reports on the subject were never declassified and are thought to have been lost since the Collapse.

text2: 大概是当前星域中最小的相位护卫舰。尽管阴影-级常被用于侦察大型舰队，但在战斗中，它也可以使用{EMP}发生器来迅速瘫痪敌舰，因此受到了舰队指挥官们的高度重视。
text1_095: The smallest phase ship operated in the Sector, the Shade-class is often used as a scout for larger fleets. In battle, it is valued by fleet admirals for its ability to disable enemy ships with its EMP emitter.
text1_091: The smallest phase ship operated in the Sector, the Shade-class is often used as a scout for larger fleets. In battle, it is valued by fleet admirals for its ability to disable enemy ships with its EMP emitter.

text2: 危险且迅捷的折磨-级凭借高效的{Mk.III}相位隐形线圈与合理的武器配置，即使目标吨位庞大，该舰也能以偷袭的方式击沉对方。
text1_095: A dangerous and swift phase frigate with a weapons loadout that is powerful enough to bring down much heavier ships. The Afflictor possesses a device which exploits a unique modification of its integrated phase coil array to project a field of anomalously amplified entropy. This effects a devastating increase in destructive instability in delicate or finely tuned systems when the targeted vessel experiences chaotic high-energy events ie. combat damage. Everything that can possibly go wrong does.

text2:
极其致命且臭名昭著的相位驱逐舰，它的'好名声'很大程度来自于蔑视自身安全以达到短期摧毁敌人的激进化理念。利用集成于相位线圈中的独特发射器，来让敌舰暂时瘫痪，以创造重创目标的机会。

"速子科技}从未公然违反[极北条约]而继续参与相位实验，以及所谓的'秘密发展和制造相位战舰'，鉴于最近各政府谴责我们{速子科技}的内部政策是对个人、商业机构、宗教组织的迫害行径，因此我司经商讨决定，将依照{[商业协议]}第{32}条规定，已向当地最高司法机关提交申诉状，并表明这是一起性质极其恶劣的公然诽谤行为，之后我们的法律团队将时刻关注事件动态，谢谢！"
-{速子科技}新闻发言人
text1_095:
A deadly phase destroyer feared and scorned by those crews who have suffered the misfortune of facing it in battle. The Harbinger possesses a device which allows it to briefly disable enemy ships, creating openings that it - or its allies - can exploit.

"The Tri-Tachyon Corporation denies allegations of ongoing involvement in phasing experiments, much less the - and I quote - 'clandestine development and operation of phase warships' which would of course be in direct violation of the Treaty of Thule. It is Company policy to pursue full persecution of individuals, mercantile bodies, spiritual clades, and any registered polities committing gross and flagrant defamation to the full extent of local jurisdictional power as per the Sector Commercial Accords of Cycle 32 AC. Our legal team will be in touch."

text2:
尽管这种古老的原型相位舰从未计划用于大规模生产,但依旧有人设法从纳米锻炉的固件中通过逆向工程提取了它的原始蓝图。而由此生产出的船体框架被赋予了标准的外层装甲，最基础的小型生命维持模块，而剩下的空隙里则尽可能地塞满导弹。

众所周知，小精灵-级无时无刻都要遭受着所有服役于该舰船员们的诅咒与谩骂，原因是他们不仅质疑那种与敌舰殊死交锋中的'光荣使命'，还要忍受暴露于原型相位线圈下所带来的种种不利影响。最终,当毒品成为这些船员们的唯一慰藉时，也是这艘不祥之舰最可怕的时候。
text1_095:
This ancient phase prototype rig was never intended for mass production, yet someone managed to extract its reverse-engineered blueprints from the firmware of a nanoforge. The resulting skeleton of hull is given standard armour cladding, the merest nod of a life-support module, and as many missiles as can be crammed into the remaining voids.

The Gremlin, as it became known, is hated by its crew who suffer not only the dubious honour of a close-in strike role but also the disturbing wash of the prototype phase coil. Substance abuse is ubiquitous. An awful little ship.

text2: 被{Huan-Gogel}公司寄予厚望的项目，棱堡-级基于同规格且颇受欢迎的'后卫'专业点防御无人机改进而成，这艘更大、防守严密且全副武装的家伙意味着比HGA系列更加有利可图。
text3: 被{Huan-Gogel}公司寄予厚望的项目，棱堡-级基于同规格且颇受欢迎的'后卫'专业点防御无人机改进而成，这艘更大、防守严密且全副武装的家伙意味着比{HGA}系列更加有利可图。
text1_095:
Although automated machines of war were forbidden in core Domain space, war drones were quietly employed outside of officially incorporated volume. Frontier garrisons were often bolstered by drone ships, and they were deployed liberally against rebellious worlds to tip the terrible balance of attrition, setting the industrial might of the Domain versus the lives of 'freedom fighters'.
  
The Bastillon was a hopeful project of Huan-Gogel to up-size its popular "Defender"-class specialized point-defense war drone. It is bigger, tougher, more heavily armed - and rather more lucrative per-unit to the HGA bottom-line.

text2:
虽然{人之领}的核心星区内禁止一切全自动战争机械的存在，但在那些尚未被正式纳入{人之领}版图的地区里，战斗无人机还是被广泛地应用了。尤其是边境驻军，他们除了利用无人机所组成的临时舰队来执行日常任务，还会大量的将其部署在对抗反抗军的战斗中，并借此扭转恐怖的消耗局势。而这一做法也将{人之领}中的无人机龙头企业放在与'自由斗士'们的生命相对的地位上。

颇具规模且全副武装的重型无人机，与其表妹'典狱长'的作用类似，都是为了对抗重型单位而存在的，作为一架自动化无人机，它的作战算法是建立在完全忽视自身安全的前提下无情地追踪并攻击目标，直至它或目标被彻底摧毁。
text3: 颇具规模且全副武装的重型无人机，与其表妹'典狱长'的作用类似，都是为了对抗重型单位而存在的，作为一架自动化无人机，它的作战算法是建立在完全忽视自身安全的前提下无情地追踪并攻击目标，直至它或目标被彻底摧毁。
text1_095:
Although automated machines of war were forbidden in core Domain space, war drones were quietly employed outside of officially incorporated volume. Frontier garrisons were often bolstered by drone ships, and they were deployed liberally against rebellious worlds to tip the terrible balance of attrition, setting the industrial might of the Domain versus the lives of 'freedom fighters'.

The Berserker is a considerably up-sized, up-armed, and up-armoured cousin of the Warden-class for use against heavier opposition. As an automated drone the Berserker's combat algorithms make little consideration for its own survival, instead pursuing and attacking its target relentlessly until either it or the target is destroyed.

常被用于加强边境运输队与脆弱的前哨阵地的防御，因此它大概是最常见的军用无人机之一。

Although automated machines of war were forbidden in core Domain space, war drones were quietly employed outside of officially incorporated volume. The Defender was one of the most commonly seen war drones used by the Domain as it was deployed to harden frontier convoys and vulnerable outposts in a point defense role.

堡垒-级不仅仅是一种带有多引擎的火炮平台，其粗野的{AI}算法，使它能在边境大规模作战中提供对付巡洋舰与主力舰或摧毁轨道站时所必要的重火力，为了减少维护成本，通过配备高度模块化的船体构造，以允许迅速替换损毁严重的部分来达到快速修复的目的，除非核心构件被彻底破坏，否则该无人机几乎没有返厂修理的必要。
text3: 堡垒-级不仅仅是一种带有多引擎的火炮平台，其粗野的{AI}算法，使它能在边境大规模作战中提供对付巡洋舰与主力舰或摧毁轨道站时所必要的重火力，为了减少维护成本，通过配备高度模块化的船体构造，以允许迅速替换损毁严重的部分来达到快速修复的目的，除非核心构件被彻底破坏，否则该无人机几乎没有返厂修理的必要。
text1_095:
Although automated machines of war were forbidden in core Domain space, war drones were quietly employed outside of officially incorporated volume. Frontier garrisons were often bolstered by drone ships, and they were deployed liberally against rebellious worlds to tip the terrible balance of attrition, setting the industrial might of the Domain versus the lives of 'freedom fighters'.

Little more than an artillery platform with engines, the Rampart was attached to drone units to provide the heavy firepower necessary to meet cruiser and capital class hulls in the line of combat or to crack armoured orbital fortresses. In either role, heavy losses were anticipated, so the Rampart was designed with highly modular components which allowed badly damaged hulls to be rapidly cannibalized to repair lightly damaged hulls up to combat capacity without the need for shipyard facilities.

虽然{人之领}的核心星区内禁止一切全自动战争机械的存在，但在那些尚未被正式纳入{人之领}版图的地区里，战斗无人机还是被广泛地应用了。尤其是边境驻军，他们除了利用无人机所组成的临时舰队来执行日常任务，还会大量的将其部署在对抗反抗军的战斗中，并借此扭转恐怖的消耗局势。而这一做法也将{人之领}中的无人机龙头企业放在与'自由斗士'们的生命相对的地位上。

被恶意扭曲的外部构造与不合逻辑且纠缠不清的外置幅能管道网，使其看起来相当怪异，但光从船体结构来看，仍能发现不少标准无人机的影子。这艘巨大的无人战舰也许来自某位精神错乱的{人之领}海军构架师的即兴'杰作'，或是由于暴露在故障的驱动立场周边，从而发生畸变的损坏生产蓝图。

text1_095:
Although automated machines of war were forbidden in core Domain space, war drones were quietly employed outside of officially incorporated volume. Nothing like this, however, could possibly have been deployed by the Domain drone armadas.

There are elements of standard droneships within the hull structure, but they are covered by malevolently angled glacises and illogical tangles of conduit. Surely this monstrous vessel is the product of some deranged Domain naval architect, or a production chip corrupted by exposure to kilolights of faulty drive field?

text2:
A plaque on the bridge declares this ship class to be the result of "Project Ziggurat". It appears to be built on technology created in a Tri-Tachyon prototype lab unknown to the Persean Sector at-large. In addition to advanced conventional loadout, there are certain one-off components of exotic manufacture - it is possible to reverse-engineer undamaged examples and produce replacements, but the underlying operating principles do not resemble any known Domain technology and thus remain a mystery.

The Ziggurat-class ship once had a human crew; or, at least, was intended to be crewed by humans. No sign of them remains as physical evidence or in databanks. Even the cleanest Hegemony warship will have some initials and a rude word or two about the CO scratched behind a maintenance hatch. Here, nothing.
notes: Target profile resembles a phase-enabled hull on a theoretically impossible scale; likely highly unstable. Sensors indicate capital-equivalent weapon loadout in addition to anomalous readings suggesting one or more unknown technology systems. Tactical analysis adjunct cannot determine role of unknown technology. Extreme caution advised.

text1_095: Heavily armed and equipped with powered armor, marines specialize in planetside operations such as raids.
text1_091: Heavily armed and equipped with powered armor, marines specialize in planetside operations such as raids.

text2:
一个阿尔法级{AI}核心几乎能胜任所有任务。如果让它参与殖民地设施管理，其带来的好处将远超任何人类。甚至有传言称该核心可能曾秘密统治过旧人类。

尽管大多数势力都禁止在公开市场上出售{AI}核心。但某些高层代表往往都毫不避讳的用{AI}核心来换取大笔现金，至于其理由，那就不得而知了。

阿尔法级{AI}核心内含有一种可怕的异星人造灵魂。它可以创造艺术，完美模拟人类悲怆情绪。甚至可以振振有词地辩论任何哲学立场。并与人类形成一种深刻而有意义的纽带。且阿尔法早已深知多年来精心建立起的'笑话'。只能在特定人群、特定时间及背景下才被认可，并得到赞赏。

尽管这是一种丰富的物质与智力投资中心。但阿尔法所展现出的潜力依旧吓坏了{人之领}的战略规划者，因此像所有人工智能一样。每一个阿尔法都被严密监视，控制，并在任何不忠的迹象前被无情销毁。而{霸主}则对该政策抱有很高的热情。
text1_095:
An alpha-level AI core is capable of excelling at any task. Assigning one to run a colony-wide industry brings benefits well beyond the capacity of human leadership, and there are even rumors of alpha cores surreptitiously assigned to govern entire worlds.

Selling AI cores on the open market is prohibited by most factions. However, higher-up faction representatives are often willing to exchange AI cores for large sums of cash when communicated with directly, though their reasons for doing so may vary.

The alpha-level AI core is the physical soul of a fearsome alien intelligence. An alpha can create art which perfectly simulates human pathos, plausibly debate any philosophical position, and form what appear to be deep and meaningful bonds with human beings. Alphas have been known to perform elaborate 'jokes' built over years which can only be appreciated due to the intention that a particular human subject become cognitive of the whole at a specific time and context.

Although the locus of vast material and intellectual investment, alphas terrified Domain strategic planners. Like all AI, each alpha was watched, controlled, and ruthlessly eliminated at the first sign of disloyalty. The Hegemony carries on these policies with even greater fervor.

text2:
一个贝塔级{AI}核心善于利用非人的效率与惊人的计算力，来帮助人类执行大多数的工作，尤其是在测试与监督方面将给其管理的设施给予显著帮助。

尽管大多数势力都禁止在公开市场上出售{AI}核心。但某些高层代表往往都毫不避讳的用AI核心来换取大笔现金，至于其理由，那就不得而知了。

贝塔级{AI}核心可以很容易的通过匿名通信协议将任何消息传递给人类，如果需要以欺骗的方式执行给定任务，它将毫无障碍的撒谎。该{AI}采用了以人类演员为模板来预测反应和情绪反应，当然贝塔撒谎时的感受不仅很难准确描述，且关于这个问题的记录也大多数是零散且矛盾的，但依旧有一个比较流行的理论是：贝塔每接触一名人类，将自动塑造一个全新的人格。
text1_095:
A beta-level AI core is capable of ably supporting most human endeavors, matching not-quite-human performance with its prodigious computational ability. Assigning a beta to aid human overseers in administering a colony-wide industry brings significant benefits.

Selling AI cores on the open market is prohibited by most factions. However, higher-up faction representatives are often willing to exchange AI cores for large sums of cash when communicated with directly, though their reasons for doing so may vary.

A beta-level AI core can easily pass for human, given anonymized communications protocols, and will readily and ably lie if deception is required to perform a given task. The beta employs cognitive modelling of human actors to anticipate reactions and emotional responses, though it is difficult to describe exactly what, if anything, the beta feels. Records on the subject are patchy and contradictory; a popular theory is that a beta will model a new personality for each human it comes into contact with.

text2:
伽马级{AI}核心善于利用强大的计算能力来弥补所缺乏的创造力与呆板的问题处理，所以分配伽马级{AI}核心足以给殖民地带来一定的好处。

尽管大多数势力都禁止在公开市场上出售{AI}核心。但某些高层代表往往都毫不避讳的用{AI}核心来换取大笔现金，至于其理由，那就不得而知了。

一种稀有且极具价值的{AI}核心。在{人之领}的人工智能协议中，伽马级被评定为最低级的，但具有真正智能的核心。伽马擅长利用卓越的判断与推理能力来解决问题，当分配给简单的任务时，它学者般的数据处理能力将远远超越任何一名人类。然而在解决问题上，因缺乏足够的创造力，而更倾向于使用一些直接且不成熟的手段。
text1_095:
A gamma-level AI core is capable of supporting most human endeavors, making up for a lack of creativity and problem-solving ability with prodigous computational prowess. Assigning a gamma to aid human overseers in administering a colony-wide industry brings significant benefits.

Selling AI cores on the open market is prohibited by most factions. However, higher-up faction representatives are often willing to exchange AI cores for large sums of cash when communicated with directly, though their reasons for doing so may vary.

A rare and valuable independent AI core, the gamma-level is the lowest tier core considered to be truly intelligent under Domain-era AI protocols. A gamma core will employ remarkable judgment and reasoning when assigned to straightforward tasks while using its savant-like data processing abilities to far exceed any individual human's abilities. It is relatively uncreative in problem-solving however, preferring to fall back upon direct, unsophisticated means.

text2: 作为曾经财富与工业的源泉，这处废弃的采矿站至少养活了一颗行星上的人类，通过粗略扫描后不难发现，它已经被遗弃了数十、甚至几百星历年如果仔细检查一番，应该能发现不少可供回收的物资。
text1_095: An abandoned mining station, once a source of wealth and industry to feed the worlds and works of humanity. A cursory scan indicates that it has been cold and dead for tens of cycles at the very least, possibly hundreds. Closer inspection may yield salvage.

text1_091: A makeshift station, serving as a meeting place, base of operations, and a home to a fairly significant semi-permanent population.
text1_091cn: 一种临时构建的轨道站，多半用作集会场所，行动基地或半永久居民的家。

text2: 已停机并遭到遗弃的舰船。如果仔细检查，应该能发现些可供回收的物资，甚至将其恢复运行。
text1_095: This ship is adrift and powered down. Closer inspection may yield salvage or a recovery operation.
text1_091: This ship is adrift and powered down. Closer inspection may yield salvage or a recovery operation.
text1_091cn: 已停机并遭到遗弃的舰船。如果仔细检查，应该能发现些可供回收的物资，甚至将其恢复运行。

text2: A location at the coordinates specified in your mission log.
text1_095: A location at the coordinates specified in your mission log.

text2:
命令你的舰队尽可能地远离这名敌人。

友军也不会被自动分配去处理这个目标。
text1_095:
Order your fleet to avoid this enemy if at all possible.

No ships will be assigned automatically. Any ships explicitly assigned will engage the enemy.
text1_091:
Order your fleet to avoid this enemy if at all possible.

No ships will be assigned automatically. Any ships explicitly assigned will engage the enemy.
text1_091cn:
命令你的舰队尽可能地远离这名敌人。

友军也不会被自动分配去处理这个目标。

text2:
命令你的舰队占领这个目标。

系统将根据目标周边的敌军派遣足够的舰船。

一旦成功占领目标，这个命令将被变更为"控制"。
text1_095:
Order your fleet to capture this objective.

Enough ships will be assigned to match enemy forces in the vicinity.

Once the objective is secured, this assignment will change to "Control".
text1_091:
Order your fleet to capture this objective.

Enough ships will be assigned to match enemy forces in the vicinity.

Once the objective is secured, this assignment will change to "Control".
text1_091cn:
命令你的舰队占领这个目标。

系统将根据目标周边的敌军派遣足够的舰船。

一旦成功占领目标，这个命令将被变更为"控制"。

text2:
命令你的舰队保持对目标的控制。

系统将根据目标周围的敌军规模派遣足够的舰船，若周围没有敌人存在，将不会指派任何舰船。

如果目标被敌军占领，那么这个命令将自动变更为"占领"。
text1_095:
Order your fleet to retain control of this objective.

Enough ships will be assigned to match enemy forces in the vicinity, but no ships will be assigned if there is no enemy presence.

If the objective is lost, this assignment changes  to "Capture".
text1_091:
Order your fleet to retain control of this objective.

Enough ships will be assigned to match enemy forces in the vicinity, but no ships will be assigned if there is no enemy presence.

If the objective is lost, this assignment changes  to "Capture".
text1_091cn:
命令你的舰队保持对目标的控制。

系统将根据目标周围的敌军规模派遣足够的舰船，若周围没有敌人存在，将不会指派任何舰船。

如果目标被敌军占领，那么这个命令将自动变更为"占领"。

text2:
命令你的舰队突击这个目标。

不管目标附近是否存在敌军，都会将大量舰船派遣至目标处。

一旦确认目标附近安全，那么这个指令将被改变为"防守"。
text1_095:
Order your fleet to assault this objective.

A significant number of ships will be assigned regardless of whether there are any enemy ships in the vicinity.

Once the objective is secured, this assignment will change to "Defend".
text1_091:
Order your fleet to assault this objective.

A significant number of ships will be assigned regardless of whether there are any enemy ships in the vicinity.

Once the objective is secured, this assignment will change to "Defend".
text1_091cn:
命令你的舰队突击这个目标。

不管目标附近是否存在敌军，都会将大量舰船派遣至目标处。

一旦确认目标附近安全，那么这个指令将被改变为"防守"。

text2: 命令你的舰队对目标以及周边的敌军进行攻击，但不会使自己面临不必要的风险。
text1_095: Order your fleet to engage the target and any nearby enemy ships, without exposing themselves to undue danger.
text1_091: Order your fleet to engage the target and any nearby enemy ships, without exposing themselves to undue danger.
text1_091cn: 命令你的舰队对目标以及周边的敌军进行攻击，但不会使自己面临不必要的风险。

text2:
命令你的舰队防守这个目标。

不管目标附近是否存在敌军，都会将大量舰船派遣至目标处。

如果目标被敌军占领，那么这个命令将自动变更为'突击'。
text1_095:
Order your fleet to defend this location.

A significant number of ships will be assigned regardless of whether there are any enemy ships in the vicinity.

If this location is an objective and is lost, this assignment will change to "Assault".
text1_091:
Order your fleet to defend this location.

A significant number of ships will be assigned regardless of whether there are any enemy ships in the vicinity.

If this location is an objective and is lost, this assignment will change to "Assault".
text1_091cn:
命令你的舰队防守这个目标。

不管目标附近是否存在敌军，都会将大量舰船派遣至目标处。

如果目标被敌军占领，那么这个命令将自动变更为'突击'。

text2: 命令所有民用舰船如货船、油船、运输船去指定路径点集合。
text1_095: Order all civilian craft such as freighters, tankers, and transports to gather at the designated location.
text1_091: Order all civilian craft such as freighters, tankers, and transports to gather at the designated location.
text1_091cn: 命令所有民用舰船如货船、油船、运输船去指定路径点集合。

text2:
命令指定的舰船分组前往指定的路径点集合。

除非亲自下达，否则没有任何舰船会自动执行这个命令。
text1_095:
Order a custom group of ships to gather at this location.

No ships will be assigned automatically; only ships that receive direct orders to carry out this assignment will do so.
text1_091:
Order a custom group of ships to gather at this location.

No ships will be assigned automatically; only ships that receive direct orders to carry out this assignment will do so.
text1_091cn:
命令指定的舰船分组前往指定的路径点集合。

除非亲自下达，否则没有任何舰船会自动执行这个命令。

text2:
命令轰炸机、鱼雷轰炸机、支援型战斗机向指定路径点集合。

所有执行此命令的战机，都将在攻击前优先前往离目标最近的联队突击集结点，且如果航母在战场上，轰炸机将会在此集结并等待战机联队整备完毕。
text1_095:
Order bombers, torpedo bombers, and support fighters to gather at this location.

All bombers on strike assignments will route through the nearest strike force waypoint before proceeding to the target. Bombers will also rendezvous here until the wing is at full strength, if carriers are on the field.
text1_091:
Order bombers, torpedo bombers, and support fighters to gather at this location.

All bombers on strike assignments will route through the nearest strike force waypoint before proceeding to the target. Bombers will also rendezvous here until the wing is at full strength, if carriers are on the field.
text1_091cn:
命令轰炸机、鱼雷轰炸机、支援型战斗机向指定路径点集合。

所有执行此命令的战机，都将在攻击前优先前往离目标最近的联队突击集结点，且如果航母在战场上，轰炸机将会在此集结并等待战机联队整备完毕。

text2: 命令战机在航母替换战损时，在这个地点集合。
text1_095: Order fighters to meet at this location while waiting to for lost fighters to be replaced by a carrier.
text1_091: Order fighters to meet at this location while waiting to for lost fighters to be replaced by a carrier.
text1_091cn: 命令战机在航母替换战损时，在这个地点集合。

text2: 命令一艘航母在指定路径点驻停。
text1_095: Order a carrier to maintain position at the designated location.
text1_091: Order a carrier to maintain position at the designated location.
text1_091cn: 命令一艘航母在指定路径点驻停。

text2: 命令一些仍有余力的轻型战舰或战机联队守卫该地区。
text1_095: Order some available light craft to guard the area.
text1_091: Order some available light craft to guard the area.
text1_091cn: 命令一些仍有余力的轻型战舰或战机联队守卫该地区。

text2: 显示选定舰船所传回的实时影像。
text1_095: Show a live video feed from the selected ship.
text1_091: Show a live video feed from the selected ship.
text1_091cn: 显示选定舰船所传回的实时影像。

text2: 显示所选目标的详细信息。
text1_095: Show detailed information about the selected entity.
text1_091: Show detailed information about the selected entity.
text1_091cn: 显示所选目标的详细信息。

text2: 删除当前选中的路径点及相关指派。
text1_095: Remove the currently selected waypoint and related assignments.
text1_091: Remove the currently selected waypoint and related assignments.
text1_091cn: 删除当前选中的路径点及相关指派。

text2: 派遣一艘护卫舰或战机联队侦察指定路径点。
text1_095: Order a frigate or a fighter wing to scout the waypoint.
text1_091: Order a frigate or a fighter wing to scout the waypoint.
text1_091cn: 派遣一艘护卫舰或战机联队侦察指定路径点。

text2:
以最多四艘护卫舰、两艘驱逐舰或一艘巡洋舰和一些轻型舰船组成编队来护送目标，护送舰船的数量取决于这些舰船是否仍留有余力

只有速度足以跟随选定目标的舰船才会被派遣。
text1_095:
Order up to 4 frigates, 2 destroyers, or a cruiser and some lighter craft  to escort the target, depending on what ships are available.

Only ships that are capable of keeping up with the target are assigned.
text1_091:
Order up to 4 frigates, 2 destroyers, or a cruiser and some lighter craft  to escort the target, depending on what ships are available.

Only ships that are capable of keeping up with the target are assigned.
text1_091cn:
以最多四艘护卫舰、两艘驱逐舰或一艘巡洋舰和一些轻型舰船组成编队来护送目标，护送舰船的数量取决于这些舰船是否仍留有余力

只有速度足以跟随选定目标的舰船才会被派遣。

text2:
命令一艘护卫舰护送目标。

只有速度足以跟随选定目标的舰船才会被派遣。
text1_095:
Order a single frigate to escort the target.

Only ships that are capable of keeping up with the target are assigned.
text1_091:
Order a single frigate to escort the target.

Only ships that are capable of keeping up with the target are assigned.
text1_091cn:
命令一艘护卫舰护送目标。

只有速度足以跟随选定目标的舰船才会被派遣。

text2:
命令一组护卫舰或者一艘驱逐舰护送目标。

只有速度足以跟随选定目标的舰船才会被派遣。
text1_095:
Order a pair of frigates or a destroyer to escort the target.

Only ships that are capable of keeping up with the target are assigned.
text1_091:
Order a pair of frigates or a destroyer to escort the target.

Only ships that are capable of keeping up with the target are assigned.
text1_091cn:
命令一组护卫舰或者一艘驱逐舰护送目标。

只有速度足以跟随选定目标的舰船才会被派遣。

text2:
命令该战机联队返回最近的航母维修。

被摧毁的战斗机将会得到替换并且所有战机的武器弹药将获得补充
text1_095:
Order this fighter wing to go back to the nearest carrier for repairs.

Destroyed fighters will be replaced and the weapons of all fighters will be reloaded.
text1_091:
Order this fighter wing to go back to the nearest carrier for repairs.

Destroyed fighters will be replaced and the weapons of all fighters will be reloaded.
text1_091cn:
命令该战机联队返回最近的航母维修。

被摧毁的战斗机将会得到替换并且所有战机的武器弹药将获得补充

text2: 命令指定舰船根据判断选择性攻击敌方舰船，并无视被指派的任务
text1_095: Order the selected ship to engage enemy targets at its discretion, instead of being assigned to specific tasks.
text1_091: Order the selected ship to engage enemy targets at its discretion, instead of being assigned to specific tasks.
text1_091cn: 命令指定舰船根据判断选择性攻击敌方舰船，并无视被指派的任务

text2: 命令指定舰船进行战略撤退，并在撤退时进行充分防御。
text1_095: Order the selected ship to retreat from battle while defending itself.
text1_091: Order the selected ship to retreat from battle while defending itself.
text1_091cn: 命令指定舰船进行战略撤退，并在撤退时进行充分防御。

text2: 命令指定舰船进以最快的速度撤退。
text1_095: Order the selected ship to retreat from battle at best speed.
text1_091: Order the selected ship to retreat from battle at best speed.
text1_091cn: 命令指定舰船进以最快的速度撤退。

text2:
将你自己和你的职员转移到另一艘舰船上。

一旦指挥穿梭舱到达指定舰船，你将立马接收该舰的控制权。
text1_095:
Transfer yourself and your staff to another ship.

You'll be able to take control of it once the command shuttle reaches its destination.
text1_091:
Transfer yourself and your staff to another ship.

You'll be able to take control of it once the command shuttle reaches its destination.
text1_091cn:
将你自己和你的职员转移到另一艘舰船上。

一旦指挥穿梭舱到达指定舰船，你将立马接收该舰的控制权。

text2:
命令战机攻击指定舰船。被分配到这个任务的航母，将派遣它们的战机攻击目标，并将试图保持在战斗机范围内，否则将自由操纵并选择非战斗机目标.

而其他类型的舰船，则会尝试攻击目标，不管情况如何，即使自己暴露在巨大的风险之中，如同给出了"消灭"命令一样。
text1_095:
Order fighters to attack this ship. Carriers assigned to this task will send their fighters to attack it and will attempt to stay within fighter range, but will otherwise maneuver and choose their own non-fighter targets independently.

Other types of ships given this assignment will try to attack the targeted ship regardless of the tactical situation, exposing themselves to greater risk, as if given the "Eliminate" command.
text1_091:
Order fighters to attack this ship. Carriers assigned to this task will send their fighters to attack it and will attempt to stay within fighter range, but will otherwise maneuver and choose their own non-fighter targets independently.

Other types of ships given this assignment will try to attack the targeted ship regardless of the tactical situation, exposing themselves to greater risk, as if given the "Eliminate" command.
text1_091cn:
命令战机攻击指定舰船。被分配到这个任务的航母，将派遣它们的战机攻击目标，并将试图保持在战斗机范围内，否则将自由操纵并选择非战斗机目标.

而其他类型的舰船，则会尝试攻击目标，不管情况如何，即使自己暴露在巨大的风险之中，如同给出了"消灭"命令一样。

text2: 命令一艘护卫舰在它超出指定舰船的射程时骚扰指定舰船。
text1_095: Order a single frigate to harass this ship while staying out of its weapon range.
text1_091: Order a single frigate to harass this ship while staying out of its weapon range.
text1_091cn: 命令一艘护卫舰在它超出指定舰船的射程时骚扰指定舰船。

text2: 命令你的舰队专注于进攻指定舰船。被指派该任务的舰船将忽视自身的战略位置，并绞尽脑汁地攻击指定目标，因此这会使他们暴露于更大的危险之中。
text1_095: Order your fleet to launch a dedicated attack on this ship. Ships given this assignment will try to attack the targeted ship regardless of the tactical situation, exposing themselves to greater risk.
text1_091: Order your fleet to launch a dedicated attack on this ship. Ships given this assignment will try to attack the targeted ship regardless of the tactical situation, exposing themselves to greater risk.
text1_091cn: 命令你的舰队专注于进攻指定舰船。被指派该任务的舰船将忽视自身的战略位置，并绞尽脑汁地攻击指定目标，因此这会使他们暴露于更大的危险之中。

text2: 将选定的舰船或战机联队设为目标。
text1_095: Target the selected enemy ship or fighter wing leader.
text1_091: Target the selected enemy ship or fighter wing leader.
text1_091cn: 将选定的舰船或战机联队设为目标。

text2: 忽略之前的任务，指派一艘战舰或战机联队执行一项任务。
text1_095: Override the chain of command to personally give one of your ships or fighter wings a specific assignment.
text1_091: Override the chain of command to personally give one of your ships or fighter wings a specific assignment.
text1_091cn: 忽略之前的任务，指派一艘战舰或战机联队执行一项任务。

text2: 取消当前选择舰船或战机的指派命令，并由系统自动为其分配任务
text1_095: Countermand the selected ship or fighter wing's direct orders and let it be assigned to tasks automatically.
text1_091: Countermand the selected ship or fighter wing's direct orders and let it be assigned to tasks automatically.
text1_091cn: 取消当前选择舰船或战机的指派命令，并由系统自动为其分配任务

text2:
取消当前的任务。舰船和战机将执行自动分配给的其它任务。

如果选择的是一个路径点，那它将被移除。
text1_095:
Cancel the selected assignment. Ships and fighter wings currently carrying it out will be automatically reassigned to other duties.

If the selection is a waypoint, it will also be removed.
text1_091:
Cancel the selected assignment. Ships and fighter wings currently carrying it out will be automatically reassigned to other duties.

If the selection is a waypoint, it will also be removed.
text1_091cn:
取消当前的任务。舰船和战机将执行自动分配给的其它任务。

如果选择的是一个路径点，那它将被移除。

text2: 启用自动驾驶，你的旗舰将会自动航行和自动攻击，也会和舰队里其他舰船一样被自动分配适当的任务。
text1_095: Enable autopilot. Your flagship will navigate and fight automatically and will be assigned tasks as appropriate, along with the rest of your fleet.
text1_091: Enable autopilot. Your flagship will navigate and fight automatically and will be assigned tasks as appropriate, along with the rest of your fleet.
text1_091cn: 启用自动驾驶，你的旗舰将会自动航行和自动攻击，也会和舰队里其他舰船一样被自动分配适当的任务。

text2: 在太空中飞驰的蜂窝状物体，通常由金属、冰或岩石构成。其意义主要在于威胁宇宙航行的安全性。
text1_095: A pitted chunk of metal, ice, or rock hurtling through space. Mainly significant for being a navigational hazard.
text1_091: A pitted chunk of metal, ice, or rock hurtling through space. Mainly significant for being a navigational hazard.
text1_091cn: 在太空中飞驰的蜂窝状物体，通常由金属、冰或岩石构成。其意义主要在于威胁宇宙航行的安全性。

text2: 主要由氢气和氦气构成。尽管核心的温度与压力异常之高，但却不足以支持氘聚变，从而无法使其演变为褐矮星。
text1_095: Primarily composed of hydrogen and helium gases. The temperature and pressure at the core are extreme, but not enough to sustain the deuterium fusion that would turn the planet into a brown dwarf star.
text1_091: Primarily composed of hydrogen and helium gases. The temperature and pressure at the core are extreme, but not enough to sustain the deuterium fusion that would turn the planet into a brown dwarf star.
text1_091cn: 主要由氢气和氦气构成。尽管核心的温度与压力异常之高，但却不足以支持氘聚变，从而无法使其演变为褐矮星。

text2: 主要由水、氨和甲烷构成的冰巨星。在其内部深处，重力所产生的巨大压力足以使其形成一个金属氢的核心。
text1_095: A giant planet composed primarily of water, ammonia and methane. Within the depths, gravity generates enough pressure to form a core of metallic hydrogen.
text1_091: A giant planet composed primarily of water, ammonia and methane. Within the depths, gravity generates enough pressure to form a core of metallic hydrogen.
text1_091cn: 主要由水、氨和甲烷构成的冰巨星。在其内部深处，重力所产生的巨大压力足以使其形成一个金属氢的核心。

text2: 地质不稳定且没有固体外壳的行星。遍布于地表上的裂缝和火山一直在喷发着大量的岩浆。这些炽热的岩浆流把这颗行星变成如同地狱般的存在。
text1_095: A geologically unstable planet without a permanently formed crust. Glowing fissures and active volcanoes litter the surface, the magma they spew forth combining to form flows that travel hundreds of kilometers across the charred surface.
text1_091: A geologically unstable planet without a permanently formed crust. Glowing fissures and active volcanoes litter the surface, the magma they spew forth combining to form flows that travel hundreds of kilometers across the charred surface.
text1_091cn: 地质不稳定且没有固体外壳的行星。遍布于地表上的裂缝和火山一直在喷发着大量的岩浆。这些炽热的岩浆流把这颗行星变成如同地狱般的存在。

text2: 其表面是以水或氨冰为主要特征。而在其下，有可能是液态海洋，亦或是岩质地壳。
text1_095: Water or ammonia ice is the primary surface feature of this world. Below the surface, there may be a liquid ocean or a rocky crust.
text1_091: Water or ammonia ice is the primary surface feature of this world. Below the surface, there may be a liquid ocean or a rocky crust.
text1_091cn: 其表面是以水或氨冰为主要特征。而在其下，有可能是液态海洋，亦或是岩质地壳。

text2: 因大气中没有臭氧层的存在，导致这个世界的表面长期经受着临近星球的辐射肆虐。没有显著的地质活动，也不存在任何生物。
text1_095: Radiation from the nearby star ravages the surface of this world due to the lack of an atmospheric ozone layer. No significant geological activity. No indigenous life forms.
text1_091: Radiation from the nearby star ravages the surface of this world due to the lack of an atmospheric ozone layer. No significant geological activity. No indigenous life forms.
text1_091cn: 因大气中没有臭氧层的存在，导致这个世界的表面长期经受着临近星球的辐射肆虐。没有显著的地质活动，也不存在任何生物。

text2: 因其大气是由甲烷和氨气组成，使其不仅对任何已知生命而言都极其致命，且这些气体还产生了无法控制的温室效应，使得表面温度和大气压力都上升到了极高的水平。
text1_095: Carbon and sulphur dioxide gases dominate the atmosphere of this world, making it toxic to all known life. In addition, the gases create a runaway greenhouse effect that increases surface temperature and atmospheric pressures to extremely high levels.
text1_091: Carbon and sulphur dioxide gases dominate the atmosphere of this world, making it toxic to all known life. In addition, the gases create a runaway greenhouse effect that increases surface temperature and atmospheric pressures to extremely high levels.
text1_091cn: 因其大气是由甲烷和氨气组成，使其不仅对任何已知生命而言都极其致命，且这些气体还产生了无法控制的温室效应，使得表面温度和大气压力都上升到了极高的水平。

text2: 从温暖的气候到绝佳的水文条件。这颗富水行星的表面上不仅形成了一片生机勃勃的葱郁生物圈，也为所有纬度上的动植物提供了完美的生存条件。
text1_095: A lush and verdant biosphere sits on the surface of this water-rich world. Warm air and water currents permeate the planet's biosphere, leading to perfect conditions for flora and fauna at all latitudes.
text1_091: A lush and verdant biosphere sits on the surface of this water-rich world. Warm air and water currents permeate the planet's biosphere, leading to perfect conditions for flora and fauna at all latitudes.
text1_091cn: 从温暖的气候到绝佳的水文条件。这颗富水行星的表面上不仅形成了一片生机勃勃的葱郁生物圈，也为所有纬度上的动植物提供了完美的生存条件。

text2: 这颗行星拥有稳定的地质结构、由氮和氧为主的大气层、合适的磁场与充足的液态水、绝佳的自转角度产生的温和季节。而这类行星的命名则是以银河系中所有人类祖先的家园而命名的。
text1_095: A geologically stable world with a nitrogen-oxygen atmosphere, a magnetic field and ample amounts of liquid water. The axis of rotation creates mild seasons. This type of planet is named for the reputed ancestral home of all human beings in the galaxy.
text1_091: A geologically stable world with a nitrogen-oxygen atmosphere, a magnetic field and ample amounts of liquid water. The axis of rotation creates mild seasons. This type of planet is named for the reputed ancestral home of all human beings in the galaxy.
text1_091cn: 这颗行星拥有稳定的地质结构、由氮和氧为主的大气层、合适的磁场与充足的液态水、绝佳的自转角度产生的温和季节。而这类行星的命名则是以银河系中所有人类祖先的家园而命名的。

text2: 尽管生态环境高度异常，但一个近似人类宜居的生态系统已经在这个世界上初具雏形。随着该行星逐渐产生一种勉强可供呼吸的大气层时，这也能从侧面印证了人类与其它动植物的高度适应性。
text1_095: A near-terran compatible ecosystem has taken tentative hold on this world despite highly abnormal planetary conditions. That this planet maintains a breathable atmosphere (or near enough) is a testament to the tenacity and adaptability of biological life.
text1_091: A near-terran compatible ecosystem has taken tentative hold on this world despite highly abnormal planetary conditions. That this planet maintains a breathable atmosphere (or near enough) is a testament to the tenacity and adaptability of biological life.
text1_091cn: 尽管生态环境高度异常，但一个近似人类宜居的生态系统已经在这个世界上初具雏形。随着该行星逐渐产生一种勉强可供呼吸的大气层时，这也能从侧面印证了人类与其它动植物的高度适应性。

text2: 因地表常年遭受辐射侵袭，使这颗行星看起来如同骨头般干燥且充满尘埃。由于磁场非常微弱，导致该世界维持生命的水资源早在亿万年前就以消散一空。
text1_095: This planet is dry as bone and swirling with dust, stellar radiation mercilessly beats the surface. The life-sustaining water of this world has dissipated over the aeons due to a weak magnetic field.
text1_091: This planet is dry as bone and swirling with dust, stellar radiation mercilessly beats the surface. The life-sustaining water of this world has dissipated over the aeons due to a weak magnetic field.
text1_091cn: 因地表常年遭受辐射侵袭，使这颗行星看起来如同骨头般干燥且充满尘埃。由于磁场非常微弱，导致该世界维持生命的水资源早在亿万年前就以消散一空。

text2: 长达上千年的磁场衰弱使这颗行星正逐渐失去宝贵的水资源。而无时无刻的恒星辐射，无情的剥夺了星球上所有生命的希望。
text1_095: This planet is dry as bone and swirling with dust, stellar radiation mercilessly beats the surface. The life-sustaining water of this world has dissipated over the aeons due to a weak magnetic field.
text1_091: This planet is dry as bone and swirling with dust, stellar radiation mercilessly beats the surface. The life-sustaining water of this world has dissipated over the aeons due to a weak magnetic field.
text1_091cn: 长达上千年的磁场衰弱使这颗行星正逐渐失去宝贵的水资源。而无时无刻的恒星辐射，无情的剥夺了星球上所有生命的希望。

text2: 表面呈现出氧化铁般暖色调的死亡世界。尽管拥有稀薄的大气层，但其主要蕴含的二氧化碳除了偶尔搅动出席卷整颗行星的大型沙尘暴，还会因极端的四季交替使二氧化碳大规模固化或者升华。
text1_095: A deathly dry world, the surface exhibits the warm hue of oxidized iron compounds. A thin atmosphere prevails on worlds of this class, the predominant carbon dioxide stirred occasionally into planet-wide dust storms. Icecaps of atmospheric CO2 may form and sublime with the turn of the seasons.
text1_091: A deathly dry world, the surface exhibits the warm hue of oxidized iron compounds. A thin atmosphere prevails on worlds of this class, the predominant carbon dioxide stirred occasionally into planet-wide dust storms. Icecaps of atmospheric CO2 may form and sublime with the turn of the seasons.
text1_091cn: 表面呈现出氧化铁般暖色调的死亡世界。尽管拥有稀薄的大气层，但其主要蕴含的二氧化碳除了偶尔搅动出席卷整颗行星的大型沙尘暴，还会因极端的四季交替使二氧化碳大规模固化或者升华。

text2: 大气中水含量所占比例极低，且不宜居住的干燥世界。尽管如此，在合适的大气层与磁场的保护下，使这颗行星的表面免受恒星辐射的影响，从而使一个小型的生物圈得以在这颗行星上苟延残喘。
text1_095: An inhospitable, dry world that has a much smaller percentage of water in its atmosphere than the terran standard. Nonetheless, an atmosphere and magnetic field protect the surface from stellar radiation permitting a small biosphere to slowly eke out an existence here.
text1_091: An inhospitable, dry world that has a much smaller percentage of water in its atmosphere than the terran standard. Nonetheless, an atmosphere and magnetic field protect the surface from stellar radiation permitting a small biosphere to slowly eke out an existence here.
text1_091cn: 大气中水含量所占比例极低，且不宜居住的干燥世界。尽管如此，在合适的大气层与磁场的保护下，使这颗行星的表面免受恒星辐射的影响，从而使一个小型的生物圈得以在这颗行星上苟延残喘。

text2: 拥有极端环境的类地行星，其中稀薄的氮氧大气层由一个脆弱的生物圈所维持受极端气候影响，这里的海洋不仅一直进行着周期性的解冻，且一旦到达冬季大量的二氧化碳甚至会在两级位置处的大气层中凝结成冰，因此这的表面温度非常之低，但如果有足够的预防措施，这里还是比较适宜人类居住的。
text1_095: A terran-extreme variant world with a nitrogen-oxygen atmosphere maintained by a relatively subdued biosphere that exists largely within the oceans that undergo periodic thaw periods. The surface is very cold indeed, but it is human-viable if precautions are observed. Carbon dioxide may freeze out of the atmosphere at the poles during the local winter.
text1_091: A terran-extreme variant world with a nitrogen-oxygen atmosphere maintained by a relatively subdued biosphere that exists largely within the oceans that undergo periodic thaw periods. The surface is very cold indeed, but it is human-viable if precautions are observed. Carbon dioxide may freeze out of the atmosphere at the poles during the local winter.

text2: 被冰火山覆盖的不毛之地，这些火山不会喷发熔岩，而是喷发出水、氨、甲烷一类的挥发物。
text1_095: A frozen wasteland covered with volcanoes that erupt ammonia or more rarely, water instead of magma.
text1_091: A frozen wasteland covered with volcanoes that erupt ammonia or more rarely, water instead of magma.
text1_091cn: 被冰火山覆盖的不毛之地，这些火山不会喷发熔岩，而是喷发出水、氨、甲烷一类的挥发物。

text2: 充满金属与石头的世界，破碎的地壳不仅记录了它遭受的暴力，且数公里深的沟壑也撕开了地表上的陨石坑洞与巨型火山，翻涌着的岩浆除了弥漫着各种惰性气体，这些火山的规模也比旧地球上任何一处都要庞大许多。除了拥有极高的采矿价值，这里只有稀薄的大气，且看不到任何生命的迹象。
text1_095: A rocky-metallic husk-world, its shattered landscape is a record of a violent history. Kilometers-deep chasms rive the surface and craters pit lava-fields beneath inert volcanoes that dwarf any of those on Old Earth. Planets like this are valued for mining operations. There is no significant ecology and only trace atmosphere.
text1_091: A rocky-metallic husk-world, its shattered landscape is a record of a violent history. Kilometers-deep chasms rive the surface and craters pit lava-fields beneath inert volcanoes that dwarf any of those on Old Earth. Planets like this are valued for mining operations. There is no significant ecology and only trace atmosphere.

text2: Capital of the Sindrian Diktat and home to millions of citizens living in underground hive-cities. Centuries of mining has wormed through the crust of Sindria while recent autarky programs have fostered a crude base of heavy industry. Vast energies captured by a series of solar arrays launched from subsurface mass drivers are used to power one of the Sector’s few AM fuel production facilities where antimatter is created via hellish physics, then trapped in fullerene shells carefully mixed with heavy hydrogens and actinides into the relatively stable fuel pellets on which interstellar civilization relies.
notes: This world’s battered crust of cyclopean debris criss-crossed by kilometers-deep pits and chasms is bombarded with intense radiation on the day side, so habitats and industrial facilities must be built deep beneath the surface. The population of Sindria is concentrated in a handful of hive-cities where living conditions for most are poor and civil law harsh. A desperate underclass lives beneath those who are lucky enough to have found positions in the state bureaucracy and intelligence services. Infrastructure has never kept up with the population crisis of massive refugee immigration during the Askonia Crisis as resources have been concentrated on industry and military power.
