text1_091cn: 辛达强权}的首都，尽管几个世纪的采矿作业已经渐渐掏空了{sindria}的地壳但却造就了该行星独有的、规模宏大的地下蚁巢型立体城市，并让数以百万的公民生活于此。最近，依照可持续发展计划，这里不仅建立起了大型的重工业原油基地，还利用大型太阳能电池阵列与复杂庞大的地核热能捕获系统，来为该地区为数不多的燃料生产设施供电。其中就包含了反物质燃料的生产，这种将混合有氘与锕的原料置入富勒烯中而合成的燃料芯块是星际文明中赖以生存的一部分。
text3_091cn: 这个世界正在崩解，数公里深的巨大坑洞、纵横交错的裂隙与白天强烈的辐射让这的栖息地与工业设施都必须建在地底深处。这的人口多数都集中在零散的蚁巢型城市里，其生活条件不仅恶劣，法律也很严苛与绝望的底层生活相比，那些能在国家官僚机构和情报部门寻得工作的则是这里的幸运儿。因绝大数资源都被集中在工业与军事力量上，使在{Askonia}危机期间涌入而来的大量难民，让基础设施不完善的{Sindria}出现了人口危机。

text2: 大气层由氨和硫化物所组成的气态巨行星。这里除了夜晚偶尔能看到大规模的闪电风暴，相比于旧地球星系中的木星来说，Salus}的体积确实要小上一些，且辐射场也更加稳定。
text1_095: A gas giant world of immense mass, the crushingly-deep atmosphere is coloured by abundant ammonia and sulphide compounds. Vast electrical storms can sometimes be seen on the night-side of this world. Salus is somewhat smaller and has relatively sedate radiation fields compared to those of Jupiter of Old Earth's system.
text1_091: A gas giant world of immense mass, the crushingly-deep atmosphere is coloured by abundant ammonia and sulphide compounds. Vast electrical storms can sometimes be seen on the night-side of this world. Salus is somewhat smaller and has relatively sedate radiation fields compared to those of Jupiter of Old Earth's system.
text1_091cn: 大气层由氨和硫化物所组成的气态巨行星。这里除了夜晚偶尔能看到大规模的闪电风暴，相比于旧地球星系中的木星来说，Salus}的体积确实要小上一些，且辐射场也更加稳定。

text2: 到处是地震和火山爆发的不稳定行星。除了表面被永不冷却的岩浆海所覆盖，四处分布的火山群将喷涌出的各种毒气、可燃气体、腐蚀气体充斥在稀薄的大气层之中。这显然不是一个欢迎其他生物来此居住的地方。
text1_095: An unstable world rocked by quakes and eruptions. Where the surface is not covered by seas of cooled lava, it is dominated by rough peaks and scattered supervolcanoes which eject toxic gases to form a tenuous and corrosive atmosphere. This is not a place welcoming to any kind of permanent settlement.
text1_091: An unstable world rocked by quakes and eruptions. Where the surface is not covered by seas of cooled lava, it is dominated by rough peaks and scattered supervolcanoes which eject toxic gases to form a tenuous and corrosive atmosphere. This is not a place welcoming to any kind of permanent settlement.
text1_091cn: 到处是地震和火山爆发的不稳定行星。除了表面被永不冷却的岩浆海所覆盖，四处分布的火山群将喷涌出的各种毒气、可燃气体、腐蚀气体充斥在稀薄的大气层之中。这显然不是一个欢迎其他生物来此居住的地方。

text2: 因受到{Salus}引力的影响，使这颗行星表面不仅残破不堪，且与世隔绝。如今在{辛达强权}控制下的{Curor}变成了一处临时采矿基地和收押囚犯的地方尽管不适宜永久居住，但仍有不少世界各地的承包商和技术员来此寻求财富。黑市中的赌场,妓院等娱乐设施在{辛达强权}政府的默许下由黑帮势力建成，而这里也成为了那些穷苦底层工人们将工资挥霍一空的好去处。
notes: 因行星地壳受到{Salus}强大的潮汐力而被挤压并破碎，导致频繁的地震与世界末日般的火山爆发。因分布广泛的间歇泉不断喷涌出挥发性气体使这颗星球拥有一层稀薄的有毒大气层，随着毒性气体与含铁化合物相结合，使{Cruor}看起来如血红般鲜艳。履带式钻探机四处漫游在相对稳定的大陆板块上，挖出各种用于出口的稀有矿石，而身后腐蚀废弃的机械堆中是一条条采矿后留下的巨大鸿沟。最近有一些谣言说，这处流动劳教所即将交给{辛达强权}的情报机构来管理。
text1_095: Cruor will always be a backwater due to its protean surface, broken and re-broken by the tidal forces of Salus. Under Diktat rule, Cruor is a world of temporary mining and prison operations. The free population is made of contractors and technicians from Volturn seeking their fortune off-world. Desperately bored workers burn their wages by partaking of the myriad vices provided by a lively black market quietly tolerated by the Diktat governor.
text3_095: The world's crust is squeezed and cracked by the powerful tidal forces of Salus, causing regular quakes and eruptions. Abundant geysers of volatile gases maintain a thin, toxic atmosphere and combine with iron compounds to give Cruor its sanguine colouration. Tracked rigs roam the more stable surface provinces, ripping out rare or merely convenient ores for export while corroding ruins of machines can occasionally be seen amidst the scars of strip-mining. Dark rumours circulate about the conditions of mobile labour camps operated by Diktat Intelligence.

text3_091cn: 因行星地壳受到{Salus}强大的潮汐力而被挤压并破碎，导致频繁的地震与世界末日般的火山爆发。因分布广泛的间歇泉不断喷涌出挥发性气体使这颗星球拥有一层稀薄的有毒大气层，随着毒性气体与含铁化合物相结合，使{Cruor}看起来如血红般鲜艳。履带式钻探机四处漫游在相对稳定的大陆板块上，挖出各种用于出口的稀有矿石，而身后腐蚀废弃的机械堆中是一条条采矿后留下的巨大鸿沟。最近有一些谣言说，这处流动劳教所即将交给{辛达强权}的情报机构来管理。

text2: 拥有原始大气层覆盖的海洋行星。其数百公里深的海洋盛产着原始单细胞生命，而广阔的藻菌复合体甚至能在太空中都能观测到。因为海洋的巨大压力使得该行星有一个类固态的水核心。
text1_095: A primitive atmosphere covers a world-ocean hundreds of kilometers deep. Its waters teem with primitive life and vast algae-analog mats can be seen by instruments from space. A core of water-ice over a rocky mantle is created by the terrific pressure of the sea.
text1_091: A primitive atmosphere covers a world-ocean hundreds of kilometers deep. Its waters teem with primitive life and vast algae-analog mats can be seen by instruments from space. A core of water-ice over a rocky mantle is created by the terrific pressure of the sea.

text2: 由乙级星球生物工程学改造的结果，volturn}拥有原始的大气和基础海洋，并已经被播种{TERRA}型原始生命种子。而它们将很大程度取代原始的微生物聚合群落。由于数百公里的海洋下面是因高压而形成的冰层，以及金属的地核，因此{volturn}的居民们只能在漂浮的微生物聚合群落上栖息着，且所有的经济是建立在复杂先进的有机农业技术之上。
notes: Volturn was envisioned as a planet of agriculture and leisure to service the now annihilated capital city-moon, Opis. Refugees from the Askonia Crisis have swelled the population of Volturn many-fold, surpassing even the numbers of Sindria and filling the floating arcologies, resort-cruisers, and terraforming barges with makeshift housing. An economy of light industry and aquaculture prevail with many products derived from the processing sea-life that has been genetically modified to flourish in the Volturnian world-ocean. A Diktat garrison maintains uneasy rule over this world of stinking algae farms and sprawling, floating slums that are a hotbed of resistance movements, esoteric cults, and criminal syndicates.
text1_095: Volturn possesses a thick atmosphere over a world-sea which has been seeded with re-engineered Terra-type life forms that have largely displaced the relatively primitive native organisms which once formed vast drifting colonial mats. Beneath the hundreds of kilometers of ocean a core of water-ice over a rocky-metallic core is formed by the immense pressure. Volturn's population lives in a diverse range of floating habitats and subsists largely on farming and processing complex organic compounds.

text3_091cn: 随着{Volturn}旧首都城市{Opis}被海水淹没，迫使{辛达强权}将这设计成一处以水产养殖与观光为主的服务卫星。受{Askonia}危机的影响，大量涌入的难民填满了建立在漂浮的微生物聚合群落上的生物工程学城市，度假村甚至是巡洋舰、改造驳船、废弃的漂浮垃圾上任何一处可以落脚的地方，也让{Volturn}人口在短时间内膨胀了数倍。轻工业和水产养殖业是这里的支柱产业，许多海产品的来源都来自经过基因改造后的各种人造或半人造生物工程学造物的养殖产出。一支强力的驻军在此维护这片充满腥臭味的巨大农场，因为这些贫民窟是最容易滋生恐怖主义、邪教、犯罪集团的温床。

text2: 由甲烷、氨所组成的冰冻行星。如岩石般坚硬的冰川在这随处可见，当被阳光照射时，冰川就会缓慢释放出稀薄的大气，而另一面只能再次沉寂于黑暗与寒冷之中。在这种极端环境下，就算陨石坑都会被'雪'所快速填平。
text1_095: A frozen world of methane and ammonia, water-ice is like rock and may be found in mountainous outcroppings and boulders. A thin atmosphere of volatiles is formed on the starward side of the planet only to freeze again on the dark side. Most craters are filled in over time as this "snow" is deposited.
text1_091: A frozen world of methane and ammonia, water-ice is like rock and may be found in mountainous outcroppings and boulders. A thin atmosphere of volatiles is formed on the starward side of the planet only to freeze again on the dark side. Most craters are filled in over time as this "snow" is deposited.

text2: 由当地反对派武装掌控，同时也是{Askonian}革命委员会的根据地。因安理会颁布的紧急条令遏制了其经济发展，而导致这里的生活条件异常艰苦。umbra}的经济主体是以回收矿藏伴生气体和对矿渣深度提炼两项产业所组成。同时{Askonian}革命委员会也会以海盗的名义来经营{umbra，因此他们的'保护费'吓跑了不少附近的独立贸易商们。而只有少部分来自{Askonia}的难民才会移民于此，除了一部分加入了革命委员会，更多则渴望在这谋求出路也正因为这些人的不断涌入，使当地基础设施不堪重负。
notes: 因过于远离{Askonia，使{Umbra}成为了颗由甲烷与氨组成的冰冻行星如岩石般坚硬的冰川在这随处可见，当被阳光照射时，冰川就会缓慢释放出稀薄的大气，而另一面只能再次沉寂于黑暗与寒冷之中。在这种极端环境下就算陨石坑都会被'雪'所快速填平。在这里，只能使用巨型采矿机械才能开采隐藏在数公里厚的冰川下的矿藏，而地底几处拥有天然地热的地区才能勉强适合人类居住。尽管在{Umbra}上的生活非常残酷,且很少有人愿意永久居住于此，但一些理想主义者和非官方志愿者仍源源不断的来到此处，带来急需的物资以及希望。
text1_095: Seat of the Askonian Revolutionary Council, a local faction of Antis. Conditions are unforgiving as harsh emergency regulations have been decreed by the Council. Economic activity consists of mining volatiles and reprocessing tailings from the abandoned core-boring project. The ARC has also allowed what might be termed "pirates" to operate from Umbra, for independent traders have been scared away by the "emergency expropriations" imposed by the ARC. Small numbers of refugees came to Umbra, straining local infrastructure, to join the revolution or expecting to find their way elsewhere.
text3_095: Far from Askonia's primary, Umbra is a frozen world of methane and ammonia where water-ice is like rock and may be found in mountainous outcroppings and boulders. A thin atmosphere of volatiles is formed on the starward side of the planet only to freeze again on the dark side. Most craters are filled in over time as this "snow" is deposited. There is some mining of heavier materials from the poor, rocky mantle buried many kilometers beneath the glacial crust. Habitats are burrowed deeply; life on Umbra is harsh and few would willingly choose to live here permanently. A trickle of idealistic out-of-system volunteers still brings much-needed supplies and hope.

text2: G2}级主序星，估计年龄为{50}亿年。表面温度六千摄氏度左右，而核心温度很可能超过{1500}万摄氏度。
text1_095: A G2 type primary sequence star, estimated age is five billion years. Surface temperature is only about six thousand degrees, while core temperature could well exceed fifteen million degrees.
text1_091: A G2 type primary sequence star, estimated age is five billion years. Surface temperature is only about six thousand degrees, while core temperature could well exceed fifteen million degrees.
text1_091cn: G2}级主序星，估计年龄为{50}亿年。表面温度六千摄氏度左右，而核心温度很可能超过{1500}万摄氏度。

text2: 这种{K}级恒星的温度与体积都要比旧地球的太阳要稍小一些。与半人马座α星{B}相似，这种位于主星序下端的恒星不仅稳定，且至少燃烧了数百亿年，因此它被认为是最佳产生宜居行星和进行地球化改造的先决条件。
text1_095: Slightly cooler and smaller than Old Earth's sun, this class K star most resembles Alpha Centauri B. It is particularly stable, burning on the lower end of the main sequence for tens of billions of years and thus considered a likely host to life-bearing and terraformable planets.
text1_091: Slightly cooler and smaller than Old Earth's sun, this class K star most resembles Alpha Centauri B. It is particularly stable, burning on the lower end of the main sequence for tens of billions of years and thus considered a likely host to life-bearing and terraformable planets.
text1_091cn: 这种{K}级恒星的温度与体积都要比旧地球的太阳要稍小一些。与半人马座α星{B}相似，这种位于主星序下端的恒星不仅稳定，且至少燃烧了数百亿年，因此它被认为是最佳产生宜居行星和进行地球化改造的先决条件。

text2: 拥有超高亮度与温度的{O}级恒星。由于其质量非常之大，使内部构成元素猛烈聚变，因此寿命极短。不久后，一场规模宏大的超新星爆发将照亮整片星系，且在变成黑洞或中子星之前，恒星内部释放出的能量，将会在强大的恒星风中喷发而出，并把较远处的所有行星从紧密环绕的轨道上推开，且在接下来的几个月内，不会有任何舰船胆敢靠近这片星系。
text1_095: A very high temperature and luminosity O-type star. Although extraordinarily massive this star is short-lived due to the hellish rate at which it fuses its constituent elements. It will quickly, for a star, explode as a supernova which may briefly outshine entire galaxies before transforming into a black hole or neutron star. The energies unleashed from the star's raging fusion heart erupt in powerful stellar winds that will strip the atmosphere from closely orbiting planets - and the hull from any starships that linger nearby.
text1_091: A very high temperature and luminosity O-type star. Although extraordinarily massive this star is short-lived due to the hellish rate at which it fuses its constituent elements. It will quickly, for a star, explode as a supernova which may briefly outshine entire galaxies before transforming into a black hole or neutron star. text2: An O-type star of extreme temperature, luminosity, mass, and volume. The supergiant star is sufficiently massive that it transitions smoothly from burning hydrogen to helium and onward. It is among the brightest candles, burning quickest and brightest before exploding as a supernova which may briefly outshine entire galaxies, bathing entire sectors in deadly radiation. The energies unleashed from the star's raging fusion heart erupt in powerful stellar winds that will strip the atmosphere from closely orbiting planets - and the hull from any starships that linger nearby.
text1_095: An O-type star of extreme temperature, luminosity, mass, and volume. The supergiant star is sufficiently massive that it transitions smoothly from burning hydrogen to helium and onward. It is among the brightest candles, burning quickest and brightest before exploding as a supernova which may briefly outshine entire galaxies, bathing entire sectors in deadly radiation. The energies unleashed from the star's raging fusion heart erupt in powerful stellar winds that will strip the atmosphere from closely orbiting planets - and the hull from any starships that linger nearby.
text1_091: An O-type star of extreme temperature, luminosity, mass, and volume. The supergiant star is sufficiently massive that is transitions smoothly from burning hydrogen to helium and onward. It is among the brightest candles, burning quickest and brightest before exploding as a supernova which may briefly outshine entire galaxies, bathing entire sectors in deadly radiation. The energies unleashed from the star's raging fusion heart erupt in powerful stellar winds that will strip the atmosphere from closely orbiting planets - and the hull from any starships that linger nearby.
text1_091cn: 拥有极端温度、亮度、质量以及体积的{O}级恒星。尽管体积庞大，但内部氢、氦元素因猛烈聚变而即将燃烧殆尽。当这颗恒星的亮度达到极致时，一场规模宏大的超新星爆发将暂时照亮整片星系，并把受影响的地区沐浴在致命的辐射之中。而恒星内涌动的能量，将会在强大的恒星风中喷发而出，并把较远处的所有行星从紧密环绕的轨道上推开，且这段时间内，不可能有任何舰船敢在这片星系附近逗留片刻。

text2: 质量比一般恒星稍低的褐矮星，且温度不足以融化内部的氢元素，但它依旧能释放出可观的电磁辐射。尽管存有争议，但这种较小的{T}型褐矮星依旧被恒星光谱划分到气态巨行星一类。与其它小行星相比，褐矮星不仅拥有更强大的磁场，且不太稳定。
text1_095: This brown dwarf is a sub-stellar primary mass which has not reached sufficient temperature to fuse hydrogen, though it radiates appreciable electromagnetic radiation due to gravitational compression. Smaller brown dwarfs are categorized with massive gas giants on a somewhat muddled spectrum rather than with a definitive threshold. The magnetic fields of the brown dwarf are powerful and potentially tumultuous compared to small planets.
text1_091: This brown dwarf is a sub-stellar primary mass which has not reached sufficient temperature to fuse hydrogen, though it radiates appreciable electromagnetic radiation due to gravitational compression. Smaller brown dwarfs are categorized with massive gas giants on a somewhat muddled spectrum rather than with a definitive threshold. The magnetic fields of the brown dwarf are powerful and potentially tumultuous compared to small planets.
text1_091cn: 质量比一般恒星稍低的褐矮星，且温度不足以融化内部的氢元素，但它依旧能释放出可观的电磁辐射。尽管存有争议，但这种较小的{T}型褐矮星依旧被恒星光谱划分到气态巨行星一类。与其它小行星相比，褐矮星不仅拥有更强大的磁场，且不太稳定。

text2: 经过超新星爆发后演变而来，拥有极致的高温与稠密的质量，且它的体积因巨大的引力而变得非常的小巧。虽然其质量等同于三个常规太阳的总和，但它的半径甚至比旧地球还要稍小一些。由于这颗中子星会快速旋转并发射出强烈的射电脉冲，因此它也被称为脉冲星。而稍微明智的星舰船长都会对其避而远之。
text1_095: This is a star that lived, died in nova, and now lives again as an extraordinarily small, hot, dense mass whose volume is maintained by the strong nuclear force rather than rote electromagnetism. Although massing up to three Solar masses, the neutron star's radius is equivalent to barely that of Old Earth. Rapidly spinning neutron stars may emit intense beams of electromagnetic radiation; these are known as pulsars. A wise starship captain would do well to avoid them.

Rapidly spinning neutron stars may emit intense beams of electromagnetic radiation; these are known as pulsars. A wise starship captain would do well to avoid them.
text1_091cn: 经过超新星爆发后演变而来，拥有极致的高温与稠密的质量，且它的体积因巨大的引力而变得非常的小巧。虽然其质量等同于三个常规太阳的总和，但它的半径甚至比旧地球还要稍小一些。由于这颗中子星会快速旋转并发射出强烈的射电脉冲，因此它也被称为脉冲星。而稍微明智的星舰船长都会对其避而远之。

text2: 由一颗大质量的恒星经过超新星爆发后的结果，是一种时空曲率大到光都无法从其视界逃脱的天体。尽管受到量子效应的影响，使黑洞能发射出可供探测的霍金辐射，但在视界之外的设备是无法检测到任何信息的。因黑洞强烈的引力会把附近的所有物体撕裂，并形成如螺旋形深渊般的吸积盘，因此极其危险。
text1_095: The result of the apocalyptic collapse of a massive star. No object can escape from the black hole, nor light itself. The black hole does however emit detectable Hawking radiation due to poorly-understood quantum effects. No information can be detected beyond the event horizon with any device known to exist in the Sector. The intense gravity of the black hole rips and tears nearby objects into an accretion disc which inevitably spirals into the gravitational abyss. Extremely dangerous.
text1_091: The result of the apocalyptic collapse of a massive star. No object can escape from the black hole, nor light itself. The black hole does however emit detectable Hawking radiation due to poorly-understood quantum effects. No information can be detected beyond the event horizon with any device known to exist in the Sector. The intense gravity of the black hole rips and tears nearby objects into an accretion disc which inevitably spirals into the gravitational abyss. Extremely dangerous.
text1_091cn: 由一颗大质量的恒星经过超新星爆发后的结果，是一种时空曲率大到光都无法从其视界逃脱的天体。尽管受到量子效应的影响，使黑洞能发射出可供探测的霍金辐射，但在视界之外的设备是无法检测到任何信息的。因黑洞强烈的引力会把附近的所有物体撕裂，并形成如螺旋形深渊般的吸积盘，因此极其危险。

text2: 巨大的{K}级恒星，因已经耗尽了核心内的氢燃料，并拥有足够的温度以及质量使其开始进行短周期的氦聚变。从技术上讲，这颗红巨星要比其它同类更大、更热，因此它更类似于经典的前域天文学中所提到的毕宿五红超巨星。
text1_095: A giant class K star which has depleted its hydrogen fuel and has reached sufficient temperature, due to sufficient mass, to fuse helium. Technically a kind of red giant, this star is more massive and hotter-burning than more common examples. Resembles the star Aldebaran known to classical pre-Domain astronomy.
text1_091: A giant class K star which has depleted its hydrogen fuel and has reached sufficient temperature, due to sufficient mass, to fuse helium. Technically a kind of red giant, this star is more massive and hotter-burning than more common examples. Resembles the star Aldebaran known to classical pre-Domain astronomy.
text1_091cn: 巨大的{K}级恒星，因已经耗尽了核心内的氢燃料，并拥有足够的温度以及质量使其开始进行短周期的氦聚变。从技术上讲，这颗红巨星要比其它同类更大、更热，因此它更类似于经典的前域天文学中所提到的毕宿五红超巨星。

text2: 在演化过程中逐渐接近末期的{M}级恒星，也是已知恒星类型中体积最大的一种在耗尽核心内所有氢燃料，并顺利度过氦聚变后，直到核心内产生出铁元素，这颗红巨星就很有可能发生超新星爆发。尽管体积非常巨大，但由于恒星表面温度相对较低，且非常明亮，因此才呈现出独特的红色。值得注意的是，经典的前域天文学中所提到过的参宿四与心宿二与这颗红巨星非常相似。
text1_095: A supergiant star in a late phase of its mayfly-short stellar life, this class M star has the largest volume of all known stellar types. It has exhausted its core's supply of hydrogen, transitioning smoothly to the fusion of helium, and is likely to proceed onward through the elements up to iron before creating a supernova. Although extraordinarily massive, the outer envelope of the star is extremely sparse and has a relatively low temperature, providing its characteristic hue. This star is casting off its constituent matter at a rapid rate and will form a spectacular nebula. Betelgeuse and Antares are examples of red supergiants known to classical pre-Domain astronomy.
text1_091: A supergiant star in a late phase of its mayfly-short stellar life, this class M star has the largest volume of all known stellar types. It has exhausted its core's supply of hydrogen, transitioning smoothly to the fusion of helium, and is likely to proceed onward through the elements up to iron before creating a supernova. Although extraordinarily massive, the outer envelope of the star is extremely sparse and has a relatively low temperature, providing its characteristic hue. This star is casting off its constituent matter at a rapid rate and will form a spectacular nebula. Betelgeuse and Antares are examples of red supergiants known to classical pre-Domain astronomy.

text2: 恒星演化末期的一种质量较低的红巨星，由于已经耗尽了核心内的氢燃料，转而在不断增大的氦核周围燃烧为数不多的氢，使这颗恒星看起来非常巨大，但由于表面温度相对较低，因此才呈现出独特的红色。
text1_095: A low-to-medium mass star in a late phase of stellar evolution, a red giant has exhausted the supply of hydrogen in its core and switched to hydrogen fusion in a shell around the now-helium core instead. While the star itself is huge, the outer envelope has a lower temperature, giving the star its characteristic hue.
text1_091: A low-to-medium mass star in a late phase of stellar evolution, a red giant has exhausted the supply of hydrogen in its core and switched to hydrogen fusion in a shell around the now-helium core instead. While the star itself is huge, the outer envelope has a lower temperature, giving the star its characteristic hue.

text2: M}级主序星，虽然又小又冷但极为常见。如果跟旧地球的太阳相比，它的质量确实太小了。
text1_095: A class M main sequence star, small and exceedingly common. These relatively cool stars often mass only a fraction of Old Earth's sun.
text1_091: A class M main sequence star, small and exceedingly common. These relatively cool stars often mass only a fraction of Old Earth's sun.

text2: 对于大多数恒星来说，白矮星的前身很可能是由红超巨星演变而来。这颗主要由碳构成的恒星因没有足够的温度来融化碳元素，使它不再由核聚变的热来抵抗重力崩溃，而是由极端高密度的物质产生的电子简并压力来支撑。
text1_095: The beginning of the end for most stars, the white dwarf was once a red giant not massive enough to fuse carbon. Extremely dense and slowly radiating away its heat as it no longer undergoes fusion reactions, its volume is supported against gravitational collapse only by electron degeneracy pressure.
text1_091: The beginning of the end for most stars, the white dwarf was once a red giant not massive enough to fuse carbon. text2:
干扰目标舰船的驱动场,瘫痪部分引擎。

通常来说它在对付全速运转的引擎时难以造成熄火,但也不是没有可能，这取决于引擎的配置,因为它至少可以干掉一个引擎。
notes: 干扰目标舰船的驱动场，来瘫痪部分引擎.

这个系统利用的各原理之间联系微弱，即便是在大崩溃之前人们对它也是知之甚少。而在如今人们的眼里它的存在就如魔法一般神秘。

notes: 暂时极大程度的提升最高航速，并稍微提升机动性.

text3_095: Provides a brief but extreme boost to top speed, along with a slight maneuverability boost.

text2: 暂时激活等离子推进器，在极短的时间内推进舰船向前移动一段距离。
notes: 在极短的时间内以极快的速度推进舰船向前移动一段距离.

text2: 一种快速装填导弹的系统。利用额外的伺服系统和自动装弹机能让舰船快速装填导弹，但激活系统将产生大量幅能。
notes: 立即装填导弹，但产生大量幅能.
text1_095: Additional servos and ordnance conveyors allow the ship to quickly reload missile weapons. Activating the system generates significant flux.
text3_095: Reloads all missile weapons quickly. Generates flux when used.
text1_091: Additional servos and ordnance conveyors allow the ship to quickly reload missile weapons. Activating the system generates significant flux.
text3_091: Reloads all missile weapons quickly. Generates flux when used.

text3_091cn: 立即装填导弹，但产生大量幅能.

text2: 引导所有武器系统的能量重定向至护盾，以极大地提高损害被吸收的效率，但这个过程中会持续产生硬幅能，即时护盾并未受到任何伤害.
notes: 禁用所有武器来大幅度降低护盾所受到的伤害,但会持续产生硬幅能.
text1_095: Redirects all power from the weapon systems to shields, greatly increasing the efficiency at which damage is absorbed. This process generates hard flux at a steady rate even if the shields are not taking any fire.
text3_095: Reduces the damage taken by shields to a minimum, but generates hard flux while active.
text1_091: Redirects all power from the weapon systems to shields, greatly increasing the efficiency at which damage is absorbed. This process generates hard flux at a steady rate even if the shields are not taking any fire.
text3_091: Reduces the damage taken by shields to a minimum, but generates hard flux while active.

text3_091cn: 禁用所有武器来大幅度降低护盾所受到的伤害,但会持续产生硬幅能.

text2: 一种高能聚焦系统，暂时提升所有能量武器的伤害。由于该系统拥有多个电容器阵列，因此允许其快速充能。
notes: 暂时提升所有能量武器的伤害.
text1_095: Briefly increases the damage dealt by all energy weapons. The capacitor array stores multiple charges, which are slowly regenerated.
text3_095: Briefly increases the damage dealt by all energy weapons.
text1_091: Briefly increases the damage dealt by all energy weapons. The capacitor array stores multiple charges, which are slowly regenerated.
text3_091: Briefly increases the damage dealt by all energy weapons.

text3_091cn: 暂时提升所有能量武器的伤害.

text2: The ship instantly teleports to any desired nearby location. Requires zero-flux boost to use.
notes: The ship instantly teleports to any desired nearby location. Requires zero-flux boost to use.

text2: 将舰船闪现至航向前方的一个地点。该系统可以缓慢累积三次传送，且冷却时间很短。
notes: 向行驶方向瞬移，可连续使用三次.

notes: 向行驶方向瞬移，可连续使用两次.

text2: 一种点防御无人机系统。通过部署大量配有激光武器的无人机来护卫舰船或自由巡逻。
notes: 部署两架配备有{IR}脉冲激光炮与{PD}激光炮的先进无人战斗机.
text1_095: Deploys a large number of laser-armed defensive drones. The drones can be ordered to closely guard the ship or roam freely around it.
text3_095: Deploys a large number of laser-armed defensive drones.
text1_091: Deploys a large number of laser-armed defensive drones. The drones can be ordered to closely guard the ship or roam freely around it.

notes: 部署大量配有轻机枪的防御无人机.

text3_095: Deploys several defensive drones armed with light machine guns.

text2: 部署几架经过武装过的探矿无人机，这些无人机不仅高度智能，还能远离母舰进行远程作业。
notes: 部署几架武装修改过的激光探矿无人机，能够远程操控.
text1_095: Deploys several combat-modified mining drones. The drones are highly autonomous and capable of operating far from the mothership.
text3_095: Deploys several combat-modified drones armed with mining lasers. Drones have long operating range.

text2: 一种感应无人机系统，通过部署装有探测器的无人机，来提高了舰船的武器有效射程与探测距离，无人机配备有离子炮。
notes: 部署能提高武器有效射程与探测距离的无人机，无人机装备有离子炮.

text3_095: Deploys a pair of drones that improve the ship's weapon and sensor range. Each drone is also armed with an ion cannon.

text3_091cn: 部署能提高武器有效射程与探测距离的无人机，无人机装备有离子炮.

text2: 激活一种可以快速装填实弹武器的先进装置，但该装置再次使用前必须重新校对并冷却完毕。
notes: 降低武器所产生的幅能，并提高所有实弹武器的射速.
text1_095: Activates an advanced - but jamming-prone - mechanism for quickly delivering ammo to the ship's ballistic weapon emplacements. The mechanism must be re-calibrated and cooled before it can be used again.
text3_095: Provides a flux cost reduction and a brief boost to the rate of fire of all ballistic weapons.

text2:
激活电磁脉冲发生器。打击附近所有的导弹、战机，且能暂时瘫痪敌舰的武器以及引擎。

不幸的是，只有关闭所有武器系统才能为该设备提供必要能源，且所释放的{EMP}脉冲电弧难以威胁到敌舰的护盾系统。
notes: 释放脉冲电弧，并迅速摧毁来袭导弹以及战机，也能暂时瘫痪敌舰的武器和引擎.但无法威胁到护盾.
text1_095:
Activates an EMP generator. Nearby missiles, fighters, weapon emplacements and engines of enemy ships are all targeted and can be disabled in short order.

Unfortunately, on-board weapon systems must be shut down to provide power for this device. The EMP pulses are also not very effective against enemy shields.
text3_095: Generates lightning arcs that quickly knock out enemy missiles, weapons, and engines within range. Mostly negated by shields.
text1_091:
Activates an EMP generator. Nearby missiles, fighters, weapon emplacements and engines of enemy ships are all targeted and can be disabled in short order.

Unfortunately, on-board weapon systems must be shut down to provide power for this device. The EMP pulses are also not very effective against enemy shields.
text3_091: Generates lightning arcs that quickly knock out enemy missiles, weapons, and engines within range. Mostly negated by shields.
text1_091cn:
激活电磁脉冲发生器。打击附近所有的导弹、战机，且能暂时瘫痪敌舰的武器以及引擎。

不幸的是，只有关闭所有武器系统才能为该设备提供必要能源，且所释放的{EMP}脉冲电弧难以威胁到敌舰的护盾系统。
text3_091cn: 释放脉冲电弧，并迅速摧毁来袭导弹以及战机，也能暂时瘫痪敌舰的武器和引擎.但无法威胁到护盾.

text2:
暂时让舰船跳入另外一个维度，即{P}空间。尽管因相位线圈持续产生的幅能仍然能使敌舰侦测到它的存在，但也意味着任何武器都无法击中不在同一维度的舰船。然而由于{P}空间不能释放幅能，因此该舰最终会因固定速率累积的幅能而迫使它回到正常空间。且在{P}空间内的舰船主观上要比正常空间的时间要快上许多。

由于相位隐形系统体积庞大，且具有显著的幅能需求，因此普遍取代护盾并作为该舰的主要防御手段。
notes: 将该舰跳入{P}空间，使其无法被任何武器所击中，但会持续产生硬幅能，且时间流速变快.
text1_095:
Temporarily moves the ship into an alternate dimension known as p-space. The ship can still be detected by its phase coil emissions, but can not be hit by any weapons. Flux can not be dissipated in p-space, resulting in a constant buildup that forces the ship to come back to normal space eventually. Subjective time passes more quickly for the ship and its crew while in p-space.

The phase cloak generator is large and has significant power requirements, and so generally replaces shields as a ship's primary means of defense.
text3_095: Moves the ship into an alternate dimension where time passes more quickly. Ship can not be hit by any weapons; builds up hard flux while active.
text1_091:

text2:
部署两架配备有{IR}脉冲激光炮与{PD}激光炮的先进无人战斗机。

更令人印象深刻的小细节就是能够在战斗中持续维修该无人机，以确保母舰可以一直拥有一名可靠的护卫。

这架无人机还配置了一种好战的贝塔级{AI，着使它拥有比那些需要遥控或者充其量只配备了伽玛级AI的无人机更远的作战半径。

该无人机史无前例的由两家公司合作设计并制造出来。由{Fabrique}轨道工厂提供底盘以及基础系统的设计方案，而{速子科技}专家则负责AI控制系统
notes: 部署一架极其先进的无人机，如果一旦被摧毁，则需要很长时间进行自我修复，并重返战场.
text1_095:
Deploys a single advanced drone that features a phase cloak, a modified phase skimmer, and an arsenal of weapons that would be impressive even on a heavy fighter.

Even more impressive is the mini-fac that's capable of producing replacement drones in combat, ensuring that the host ship is not without escort for long.

The drone also possesses an aggressive delta-level AI personality that allows it to roam much farther from the mothership than most other drone systems - that are either entirely on remote-control, or feature a sub-gamma personality at best.

This design is also unique in that it was created through the cooperation of two rival corporations. Fabrique Orbitale provided the chassis and system designs, while Tri-Tachyon experts were responsible for the controlling AI.
text3_095: Deploys a single highly advanced drone. The drone will be slowly rebuilt if it's destroyed.

text2: Deploys replacement fighters that can fight for a short time before returning to the carrier. Can temporarily raise the number of deployed fighters above the maximum wing size.
notes: Deploys replacement fighters that can fight for a short time before returning to the carrier. Can temporarily raise the number of deployed fighters above the maximum wing size.

text2: 给所有部署在外的战机发送实时目标数据，来暂时提高它们所造成的伤害。

notes: 将所有部署在外的战机立即召回至航母机库之内，来使它们能迅速补充弹药或修复战机.

text1_091: Teleports all fighters back to the carrier, allowing them to be quickly refitted and relaunched.
text3_091: Teleports all fighters back to the carrier, allowing them to be quickly refitted and relaunched.
text1_091cn: 将所有部署在外的战机立即召回至航母机库之内，来使它们能迅速补充弹药或修复战机。
text3_091cn: 将所有部署在外的战机立即召回至航母机库之内，来使它们能迅速补充弹药或修复战机.

text2: 空无一物的开阔区域，这处不显眼的地方是星系超波场中所受影响最低的位置。相对较少的干扰使得它非常适合用于放置各种利用超波技术的设施。
text1_095: This otherwise unremarkable point in the surrounding vast emptiness is a local minimum in the star system's hyperwave field. The relative lack of interference makes it uniquely suited for the placement of hyperwave-tech-using structures.
text1_091: This otherwise unremarkable point in the surrounding vast emptiness is a local minimum in the star system's hyperwave field. The relative lack of interference makes it uniquely suited for the placement of hyperwave-tech-using structures.
text1_091cn: 空无一物的开阔区域，这处不显眼的地方是星系超波场中所受影响最低的位置。相对较少的干扰使得它非常适合用于放置各种利用超波技术的设施。

text2: 基于{人之领}技术建成的通信基站，该超波通信阵列能以超光速在星系间传输和接受数据。因适合{FTL}传输的超波脉冲已被证实存在破坏生物{DNA}的巨大隐患，所以它们一般都建立于远离栖息地的偏远位置。
text1_095: A Domain-era technology used primarily on the frontier, this is a hyperwave communications array which transmits and receives data between star systems at faster-than-light speeds. The rapidly pulsing hyperwaves suitable for FTL data transmission have been shown to damage DNA so these relays are always stationed away from habitats.
text1_091: A Domain-era technology used primarily on the frontier, this is a hyperwave communications array which transmits and receives data between star systems at faster-than-light speeds. The rapidly pulsing hyperwaves suitable for FTL data transmission have been shown to damage DNA so these relays are always stationed away from habitats.
text1_091cn: 基于{人之领}技术建成的通信基站，该超波通信阵列能以超光速在星系间传输和接受数据。因适合{FTL}传输的超波脉冲已被证实存在破坏生物{DNA}的巨大隐患，所以它们一般都建立于远离栖息地的偏远位置。

text2: 效仿于{人之领}中继站而建成的设施，虽利用了时下被认为最先进的技术,但这种临时性的通讯中继站即便能发射超光速通讯信号，其传输速度仍弱于前者，且偶尔发出的幽灵通讯流也会让最老练的船长做上一整晚的噩梦。
text1_095: An imitation of the Domain-era counterpart, constructed using what passes for the state of the art in the Sector. Nonetheless, a makeshift comm relay is capable of facilitating faster-than-light comms between star systems, even if the transmission speeds are less than ideal and the occasional phantom comm streams picked up give nightmares to even the most seasoned operators.
text1_091: An imitation of the Domain-era counterpart, constructed using what passes for the state of the art in the Sector. Nonetheless, a makeshift comm relay is capable of facilitating faster-than-light comms between star systems, even if the transmission speeds are less than ideal and the occasional phantom comm streams picked up give nightmares to even the most seasoned operators.
text1_091cn: 效仿于{人之领}中继站而建成的设施，虽利用了时下被认为最先进的技术,但这种临时性的通讯中继站即便能发射超光速通讯信号，其传输速度仍弱于前者，且偶尔发出的幽灵通讯流也会让最老练的船长做上一整晚的噩梦。

text2: 基于{人之领}技术建成的高清被动监测阵列，内置的发射器能以超光速在星系间进行实时数据传输。而这将有益于附近舰队的常规传感器探测。
text1_095: A Domain-era technology, this is a super-high-resolution passive monitoring array with a transmitter capable of real-time, faster-than-light data transmission within the star system. The data is useful to supplement the regular sensor readings made by fleets.
text1_091: A Domain-era technology, this is a super-high-resolution passive monitoring array with a transmitter capable of real-time, faster-than-light data transmission within the star system. The data is useful to supplement the regular sensor readings made by fleets.
text1_091cn: 基于{人之领}技术建成的高清被动监测阵列，内置的发射器能以超光速在星系间进行实时数据传输。而这将有益于附近舰队的常规传感器探测。

text2: 采用时下最先进的技术而建成的临时传感器阵列，尽管弱于其前辈，但它依旧能被动监测整片星系，并为附近友军舰队提供高清实时数据，而这些数据将有助于增强其舰队常规传感器的探测效果。
text1_095: Built using the best technology available in the Sector, a makeshft sensor array is nonetheless capable of passively monitoring the entire star system and has a transmitter capable of real-time, faster-than-light data transmission to friendly fleets within. The data is useful to supplement the regular sensor readings made by fleets.
text1_091: Built using the best technology available in the Sector, a makeshft sensor array is nonetheless capable of passively monitoring the entire star system and has a transmitter capable of real-time, faster-than-light data transmission to friendly fleets within. The data is useful to supplement the regular sensor readings made by fleets.
text1_091cn: 采用时下最先进的技术而建成的临时传感器阵列，尽管弱于其前辈，但它依旧能被动监测整片星系，并为附近友军舰队提供高清实时数据，而这些数据将有助于增强其舰队常规传感器的探测效果。

text2: 基于{人之领}技术建成的导航信标，能被动监控整片星系内的超视场，还能将计算后的导航信息传输给附近友方舰队，而这些读数将有助于舰队的航行效率。
text1_095: A Domain-era technology, a nav buoy monitors the in-system hyperfield and is capable of transmitting its findings to friendly fleets in-system. The data readings are pristine and of great use in configuring drive fields.
text1_091: A Domain-era technology, a nav buoy monitors the in-system hyperfield and is capable of transmitting its findings to friendly fleets in-system. The data readings are pristine and of great use in configuring drive fields.
text1_091cn: 基于{人之领}技术建成的导航信标，能被动监控整片星系内的超视场，还能将计算后的导航信息传输给附近友方舰队，而这些读数将有助于舰队的航行效率。

text2: 采用时下最先进的技术建成的临时传感器阵列，尽管弱于其前辈，但它依旧能被动监控整片星系的超视场，并将计算好的数据传输给附近的友方舰队，不过这些读数并不十分可靠，但仍能提高其动态驱动器的效力。
text1_095: Built using the best technology available in the Sector, a nav buoy monitors the in-system hyperfield and is capable of transmitting its findings to friendly fleets in-system. The data is often somewhat unreliable but still useful in making on-the-fly drive field adjustments.
text1_091: Built using the best technology available in the Sector, a nav buoy monitors the in-system hyperfield and is capable of transmitting its findings to friendly fleets in-system. The data is often somewhat unreliable but still useful in making on-the-fly drive field adjustments.

text1_095: An orbital station constructed as a custom campaign entity with a "station" tag.
text1_091: An orbital station constructed as a custom campaign entity with a "station" tag.

text2: 没有生命迹象的岩质星球，除了稀薄到几乎没有的大气，满目疮痍的地表也证明了它曾受到的万年陨石的洗礼。因没有显著的地磁场或地质运动，使这里的岩浆很顺利的就将大地切开，并汇聚到远古留下的巨大陨石坑里，以形成规模宏大的岩浆海洋。
text1_095: A lifeless rocky world, the battered surface tells an aeons-long story of intermittent meteor bombardment. What atmosphere there is clings to the scarred crust in near-vacuum. There is no significant magnetic field or tectonic activity. Deep regolith prevails, crossed by lava channels and spotted by ancient lava seas formed by especially large impacts.
text1_091: A lifeless rocky world, the battered surface tells an aeons-long story of intermittent meteor bombardment. What atmosphere there is clings to the scarred crust in near-vacuum. There is no significant magnetic field or tectonic activity. Deep regolith prevails, crossed by lava channels and spotted by ancient lava seas formed by especially large impacts.

text2: 贫瘠与高度致命的辐射使这颗行星表面没有任何生命迹象。致命的环境甚至连机器人都感觉浑身不适，为了满足那些愿意来此居住的疯子们，任何栖息地都必须建立在极深的地下以达到基本的生存条件。
text1_095: Barren and highly irradiated, this planet is not only devoid of life but is a harsh environment even to hardened robotic operations due to the awesome energies inflicted upon its surface. Any habitat would have to be constructed deeply indeed for anyone mad enough to live here.
text1_091: Barren and highly irradiated, this planet is not only devoid of life but is a harsh environment even to hardened robotic operations due to the awesome energies inflicted upon its surface. Any habitat would have to be constructed deeply indeed for anyone mad enough to live here.

text2: 这片生机盎然的葱郁生物圈就是{Jangala}的生态系统。尽管该行星上的农场与海洋经常受到巨型风暴的影响，但这里依旧是有机物、食品、奇异外来生物原材料的主要产地。也被大多数{卢德教会}的信徒誉为'神圣之地'。
notes: 最初是一处生物研究与旅游中心，但随着开发进度的加快，使数百万平方公里的森林被夷为平地，并被遍布大型机械收割机的种植基地所替代。尽管如此，由于空气中的孢子浓度远超正常水平数倍，因此所有人类必须佩戴生物过滤口罩才能进行地表勘探以及净化工程的施工，且茂盛的本土丛林因极其凶猛的生长速度，迫使{Jangala}空间站必须定期利用轨道炮来焚烧以阻截其继续扩张，因此这颗行星并不是外界所描述的'人类天堂'
text1_095: Jewel of the Corvus system, Jangala possesses a lush native biosphere. The world's farms and seas, often hidden by the churning cyclones of megastorms, are a major source of organic feedstock, food products, and exotic xenobiological materials. Considered holy by most Luddic sects.
text3_095: Initially a center of xenobiological study and tourism, exploitation followed discovery and millions of square kilometres were razed then covered by plantations tended by massive robotic harvesters.  But it is no paradise for humans, requiring biofilter masks and a decontamination process for surface visits. The riotous native jungle must be held back to this day by periodic orbital burns from Jangala Station.
text1_091: Jewel of the Corvus system, Jangala possesses a lush native biosphere. The world's farms and seas, often hidden by the churning cyclones of megastorms, are a major source of organic feedstock, food products, and exotic xenobiological materials. Considered holy by most Luddic sects.

text2: 拥有轨道城市、海军码头以及贸易港口的{Jangala，无疑是世界文明与文化的中心。也是{Ecovacs}星系的重工业基地、交通枢纽站、{霸主}军事区的所在地
notes: 其中巨大的分层结构基本由：巨大的环形实验室、重工业机库/船坞、商业广场、大都市地区所组成，而任何靠近的商业或军事舰船都会被几处配有大型通信阵列和武器吊舱的高塔所监控。
text1_095: Orbiting megacity, naval yard, and port; the unquestioned cosmopolitan center of civilization and culture in the Corvus system as well as the seat of the Hegemony military district encompassing the local systems. Heavy commercial and naval traffic swarm the station at all times.
text3_095: Formed of a vast tiered structure, the first ancient fueling and repair gantries are hidden among corroded industrial hangars that lie in the shadow of a huge ring of laboratories and associated support systems. Higher still, commercial concourses, metroplex districts, and many-winged shipyards are all watched over by a command & control spire bristling with communications arrays and weapon pods.
text1_091: Orbiting megacity, naval yard, and port; the unquestioned cosmopolitan center of civilization and culture in the Corvus system as well as the seat of the Hegemony military district encompassing the local systems. Heavy commercial and naval traffic swarm the station at all times.

text2: 这颗沙漠行星是'大崩塌'前地球化改造失败后的产物。人口则是由一些{自由联盟}的移民、罪犯或疯子构成。尽管{霸主}对其声称拥有主权，但也不过是派遣数支巡逻队来此清剿海盗，就没有任何下一步的管理措施。不过较少的关税使得这里仍有一些商业活动的存在。
notes: 因曾有{Barad}卫星的保护而让{Asharu}得以保留一层由冰蒸发后的气体所组成的稀薄大气。得天独厚的条件让其被评为适合地球化改造的候选之一。但'大崩塌'的到来，让疯狂的{卢德左径}利用行星杀手将这处仅存的树荫摧毁。并让失去保护的{Asharu}因高温导致其生态资源迅速枯竭，现也仅有少数的顽强动植物与原住民在巨型沙丘间的群山中挣扎求生，然而令人绝望的是，如今这些沙丘正慢慢吞噬着那些未能建成的城市基础。
text1_095: A desert planet, product of an abortive terraforming project from before the Collapse. Populated by a few fiercely independent settlers, criminals, and oddballs. The Hegemony technically claims dominion over Asharu but maintains no permanent administration, sending patrols only to chase down pirates or impose heavy but infrequent tariffs on what little commercial activities remain.
text3_095: In better times Asharu was a model terraforming prospect: A solar shade lowered the surface temperature while ice launched from the moons of Barad left shining vapour trails to fall as rain from the skies. Alas the chaos of the Collapse halted the ice and suspected Luddic sabotage destroyed the shade. Investment dried up and now only few hardy lifeforms (including a handful of human settlers) cling to existence in the sheltering mountains between the vast dunes that are slowly retaking the foundations of cities never built.

text2: 因拆船业是该地区的中心支柱产业。让不少{霸主}等其它星系势力将报废船只送往这里。而{KO联合实业}也花费重金，买下这颗行星的管理权，并利用全新的回收技术舰船重建以及{(不可靠消息)}从废旧的{AI}核心中搜集情报，来赚取财富。
notes: 几个世纪以来，在这个贫瘠的世界里，被剥离的船体外壳在早已冷却的岩浆海中沉睡已久，而一些特殊的反应堆核心则被遗弃在隔离坑里，这些核反应堆的辐射强度高到即便在很远的距离内都能被检测到。被雇来的工人住在基于巨型陨石坑所建造的地下城市里，这些建筑则被闪闪发光的太阳能电池板和通往边远加工厂和材料堆场的管道所包围着。
text1_095: A major center of shipbreaking in this region of the Sector, hulks are consigned to scrapping here by the Hegemony Navy and many other clients from among the Sector core worlds. The Ko Combine has purchased the rights to planetary administration under their corporate charter and has rebuilt their fortune on employing novel recycling techniques, ship-reconstruction, and (some say) scraping intelligence from dead pseudo-AI cores.
text3_095: Centuries of stripped starship hulls rest on the long-cold lava seas and regolith plains of this barren world. Some especially radioactive reactor cores are left in quarantined pits that glow with detectable radiation ticking on long-range scans. Workers employed by the industrial operations live in vast crater-arcologies, underground cities ringed by glittering solar arrays and spurs of transport tubes leading to outlying processing facilities and material yards.

text2: Dirty ammonia snow falls in fits and flurries from the thin atmosphere of Nomios. The drifts are small and mostly cleared from the habitats' armoured landing-bay doors by battered crawler drones operated by the strange ruling bureaucracy.
text1_095: Dirty ammonia snow falls in fits and flurries from the thin atmosphere of Nomios. The drifts are small and mostly cleared from the habitats' armoured landing-bay doors by battered crawler drones operated by the strange ruling bureaucracy.
text1_091: Dirty ammonia snow falls from the thin atmosphere in fitful storms on Nomios, but the drifts are small and mostly cleared away from the armoured landing-bays of the ruling bureaucracy by crawler drones. This is a strange insular polity displays disproportionate wealth.
text1_091cn: 作为{Agreus}拆船行业的分支，著名的{Nomios}造船厂可翻新或重组任何打捞上的废旧船只，也使此地被大量建造机械、巨型货物升降机、机器人流水线，炼油厂以及化学品处理厂所塞满。在一阵阵暴风雨中，肮脏的氨雪从稀薄的大气层中落下，但因工业中心释放出的废热将这些雪花融化了大半，因此地表也只有少量的积雪。

text2: 与其它以氢为主的气态巨行星不同，这颗巨大的行星由大量较重的挥发物组成强风无时无刻席卷着气流中的碳氢化合物与漂浮着的氨云，并在极端的压力下形成了一片充满'异国情调'的氨海。
text1_095: A giant planet composed of a large proportion of heavier volatiles than the more massive classical hydrogen-dominated gas giants. High winds sweep ammonia clouds over great storms and upwellings of hydrocarbons from the gradual transition to water-ammonia seas that lay atop exotic ices formed by the extreme pressure and high gravity.
text1_091: A giant planet composed of a large proportion of heavier volatiles than the more massive classical hydrogen-dominated gas giants. High winds sweep ammonia clouds over great storms and upwellings of hydrocarbons from the gradual transition to water-ammonia seas that lay atop exotic ices formed by the extreme pressure and high gravity.
text1_091cn: 与其它以氢为主的气态巨行星不同，这颗巨大的行星由大量较重的挥发物组成强风无时无刻席卷着气流中的碳氢化合物与漂浮着的氨云，并在极端的压力下形成了一片充满'异国情调'的氨海。

text2: 霸主}的后勤中心，其建设目的是为了满足当地舰队补给需求，进而以{Arcadia}战略驻地为跳板向周遭星系投射军事力量。核心结构上实用而优雅的巨大圆环不仅引人注目，且这些作为清理空间站挥发物的虹吸设施，它的建造历史甚至可以追溯到'大崩塌'前。为了保护至关重要的战略物资免受突袭的风险，大量来自{Agreus}的，配备有粗制武器吊舱与装甲结构的翻新舰船不断巡逻于此。
text1_095: This is a Hegemony logistics center built to supply fleets capable of projecting power throughout the strategically vital Arcadia system. The utilitarian grace and sweeping rings of its core construction date the original station's volatiles siphoning facilities to before the Collapse. Later, crude weapons pods and armoured nodules assembled from hulks destined for Agreus were been added in response to the risk of surprise raids against this vital concentration of materiel.

text2: 由大量复杂的碳基化合物及其衍生物组成。被广泛应用于塑料、燃料、溶剂、聚合物、食品，生物技术与其它生活必需品等领域中。
text1_095: Bulk complex carbon-based molecules and derivatives thereof with applications in plastics, fuels, solvents, polymers, food products, biotech, life support, and a vast array of other necessities.

text1_091: Rare isotopes of lighter elements - such as deuterium - with critical applications in fuel production and other advanced industrial processes.

text2: 包括亚铁和普通有色金属的矿石。必须被提炼加工后才能被应用于工业用途。

text1_091: Refined forms of both ferrous and common non-ferrous metals used in most construction and goods production. Ingots follow traditional Domain standards.

text2: 用于在工业中吊装任何物质的标准化模块重型机械。可接受手动操控或套用常见的设计模板格式自动执行，以及被远程网络遥控。
text1_095: Various standardized modules for manipulating matter on an industrial scale. They accept manual input, most common design template formats, or can be slaved to network control.
text1_091: Various standardized modules for manipulating matter on an industrial scale. They accept manual input, most common design template formats, or can be slaved to network control.

text2: 自工业化航天文明建成以来，这些经大规模轻工业生产出的服装、小工具、配件、用品、使人们过上了舒适的生活。
text1_095: These are the mass-produced clothing, gadgets, wares, and goods that have enabled people to live a comfortable life since the establishment of industrialized spacefaring civilization.
text1_091: These are the mass-produced clothing, gadgets, wares, and goods that have enabled people to live a comfortable life since the establishment of industrialized spacefaring civilization.

text2: Organ replacement is a well-established practice but the materials are delicate and growing them a fickle process. There’s always a market in healthy organs and always a source if one doesn’t ask too many questions.

text1_091cn: 人们现在已经普遍接受器官移植这种行之有效的方法。但健康而合适的器官总是那么稀有，如果你不在乎来源是否合法，那就去黑市瞧瞧吧。

text2: 虽在绝大数星球被禁止贩卖，但这些令人眼花缭乱的化学工艺，让那些寻求刺激、强化意识，或逃避悲惨生活的人们沉迷其中。
text1_095: Banned on some worlds, the "chemical arts" include a dizzying array of products sought by those seeking a bit of fun, expanded consciousness, or simply an escape from their miserable lives.

text2: Armaments ranging from heavy squad-level weapons to mechs, tanks, and hovercraft. Private use is banned on most worlds. Largely disassembled and not suitable for use in quick raids.
text1_095: Armaments ranging from heavy squad-level weapons to mechs, tanks, and hovercraft. Private use is banned on most worlds. Largely disassembled and not suitable for use in quick raids.

text2: 混合了多种旧地球物种和一点想象力而创造出的生物，它们主要栖息在{Volturn}海底深处的破碎海床上，据说味道非常独特。
text1_095: A mix of several Old Earth species and a little imagination produced this creature which grows wild in the crushing depths of Volturn's sea-floor. The flavor is said to be exceptional.
text1_091: A mix of several Old Earth species and a little imagination produced this creature which grows wild in the crushing depths of Volturn's sea-floor. The flavor is said to be exceptional.

text2: 卢德家具是一种罕见且极为珍贵的木制工艺品，由自然生长的木材作为原料，并由工艺大师以及他亲传的学徒联合手工打造。
text1_095: Constructed from wood grown naturally on planets and made by hand-tools according to methods passed from master to apprentice, Luddic furniture is a rare and highly prestigious possession in the Sector.
text1_091: Constructed from wood grown naturally on planets and made by hand-tools according to methods passed from master to apprentice, Luddic furniture is a rare and highly prestigious possession in the Sector.

text2: 较低档次或在技术上经常有缺陷，以及具备"出口标准"的船体与军备。经常应用于商队护卫与基础星系巡逻队中，但如想在势力间大批交易顶级星舰材料仍无疑是痴人说梦。
text1_095: Low-tier and often technically defective - "export grade" - ship hulls and armaments which are sufficient to equip mercantile convoys and form basic system defense patrols. High-volume trade in top tier starship materiel is virtually non-existent across faction lines.

text2: Yggdrasil}气态巨行星的卫星，由于巨大的潮汐力不断加热并搅动{Nidhogg}的内部结构，使大量裂缝与火山遍布于星球表面，在这里，被岩浆烧焦或淹没的大地成为了最正常不过的风景。
text1_095: A geologically unstable moon due to proximity to the gas giant Yggdrasil, tidal forces endlessly heat and churn the innards of Nidhogg. Fissures and volcanoes dot the surface and the lava they spew flows for many kilometers across the charred crust.

text2: A lifeless and barren rocky-silicate moon with a wisp of atmosphere that incandesces faintly when struck by Yggdrasil’s radiation belts.
text1_095: A lifeless and barren rocky-silicate moon with a wisp of atmosphere that incandesces faintly when struck by Yggdrasil’s radiation belts.
text1_091: A lifeless and barren rocky-silicate moon with a wisp of atmosphere that incandesces faintly when struck by Yggdrasil<U+0092>s radiation belts.
text1_091cn: 生命荒芜且贫瘠不堪，这颗主要由硅酸盐构成的卫星，尽管拥有稀薄的大气层但因过于靠近{Yggdrasil}而常年遭受辐射侵袭，使这颗星球反射出淡淡光芒

text2: 充满水和氨冰的深沟巨壑遍布于星球表面，而在地表之下、在冰层与硅酸盐构成的地壳之间，存在着一片没有生命的海洋。'大崩塌'后，尽管{霸主}颁布的战略政策提高了对该星球重建项目与移民的资助标准，且获得了众多退役军人的大力支持，但依旧有部分圆顶城市因无人居住而遭到遗弃。随着最近{霸主}通过赠款的方式，刺激了当地颇具潜力的挥发物开采作业的发展，而被吸引来的诸神黄昏集团与{速子科技}的项目工作人员以及工人使日渐繁荣的{Raesvelg}的夜生活逐渐喧嚣了起来。
text1_095: Water and ammonia ice form the immense rifts and chaotically furrowed plains of this world. Below the surface, small pockets of lifeless liquid ocean are trapped between the ice and a crust made of rocky silicates. Most of the sprinkling of domed cities remain abandoned since the Collapse, though recent Hegemony strategic policy has encouraged re-industrialization and settlement, especially by the numerous Hegemony military veterans. Crew and workers on leave from the nearby Ragnarok Complex and Tri-Tach projects supports a rowdy nightlife and black market. Volatiles mining is encouraged by Hegemony development grants.

text2: 地壳是由氮气和甲烷冰所组成，而表面则被大量硅酸盐与冰幔覆盖得严严实实。由于{速子科技}获得了{霸主}颁发的独家开发许可证，使这里只有一处庞大的加工厂矗立于此，明面上是开采挥发性气体与建设一些基础设施，不过背地里有传言称这里的一处秘密研究机构正从事非法实验，但派遣至该处的调查员至今没有发现任何确实证据。
text1_095: Drifts of nitrogen and methane ice form most of the crust over a rocky silicate/ice mantle which pierces the cowl of this frozen moon here and there. The Hegemony has granted Tri-Tachyon a license for exclusive development, consisting primarily of a sprawling processing plant for volatiles siphoned from Niflheim and the requisite support infrastructure. Rumours abound that it's all the cover story for a secret research facility performing science deemed illegal under Domain law precedence, but inspectors have never reported anything untoward.

Rumours abound that it's all the cover story for a secret research facility performing science deemed illegal under Domain law precedence, but inspectors have never reported anything untoward.

text2: {霸主}的悲伤之地，除了一支为防止{英仙座联盟}入侵的守备部队驻扎于此，Ragnar}的综合大楼内还有一批等待翻新作业的工人。这些与超级军团签订回收协议的人们，唯一任务就是日以继夜的在这拆除废旧船只以重新组装利用并送往{Arcadia}等待这些破船重新报废。这里由一位年迈的高级指挥官管理他唯一需要做的就是在这安度晚年。
notes: 绰号'坟墓'。破碎的弧形机库与龙门架将大量报废船只排列整齐，并等待检查。这里除了安检员手中的照明，与焊枪所发出的亮光，大部分时间都处于黑暗之中。但在这片黑暗里，不仅隐藏着一支庞大的舰队，其中心附近还有一处安置着民用承包商、海军船员、海军陆战队以及{霸主}管理人员的{HAD}圆顶城市。
text1_095: The boneyard of the Hegemony; in addition to the garrison stationed here to support system patrols and a fleet-in-being to discourage League incursions, the Ragnar complex stores ship hulks awaiting refurbishing or the haul to Arcadia for ship-breaking, a task generally contracted to friendly megacorps. The station is traditionally commanded by an aging senior officer sent to quietly live out their mediocrity.
text3_095: Nicknamed "The Tomb", broken arcs of hangars and gantries clutch row upon row of mothballed hulks awaiting inspection. Most are dark, lit only by inspection crews and the welding torches of armourers removing materiel. Hidden near the centre of the shadow armada lies a stack of hab-rings populated by civilian contractors, navy crew, marines, and Hegemony administration.

text2: {速子科技}主动筹资在这建立了一处据点，其主要目的是运用欧阳工业的虹吸技术来'开采'这颗气态巨行星。虽然会消耗庞大的能源，可一旦将其中的重同位素稳定下来，就能实现自我维持。如果能开采出和{Niflheim}同种类的重型混合挥发物，那么将很可能直接送往{Skathi}卫星上被加工成有用的产品
text1_095: The product of a Tri-Tachyon initiative to modify the common gas-giant "mine" which siphons gases using the Ouyang Process which, although energy-hungry, becomes self-sustaining once a steady pull of heavy isotopes is attained. From Niflheim a particularly heavy mix of volatiles can be drawn, and these are processed on the moon of Skathi into countless useful forms.

text2: A small terrestrial planet, Maxios was once the cosmopolitan hub of the system. Now spotted with ruins and impacts both ancient and fresh, the crumbling orbital defense system provides only intermittent coverage. Civilization is collapsed and the current population is unknown. There is no stable ruling polity. Looters and survivors clash occasionally, the weapons-blink and electromagnetic noise of low-level combat sputtering like a gas giant’s electrical storms.

text1_091cn: 小型类地行星。尽管{Maxios}曾是该星系重要的商业枢纽，但如今剩下的一片残垣断壁和高空中摇摇欲坠的轨道防御系统，无声地诉说着往日的喧嚣与繁华。自崩溃后，目前该行星的总人口依旧未知。由于没有稳定的政权，使掠夺者和幸存者之间偶尔会发生小规模冲突，也让这里的枪声与电磁噪音像气态巨行星的风暴一般常见。

text2: 由于这颗气态巨行星非常靠近其母恒星，因此可以推论它很可能是在外部星系形成的，后因遭到未知原因脱离了原轨道，而成为了一颗流浪行星并迁移于此主要由氢、氦两种气体所组成，且核心内的温度与压力是非常高的。
text1_095: Anomalously close to its parent star, this gas giant probably formed in the outer system and later migrated inward due to a chance encounter with some rogue cosmic mass. Primarily composed of hydrogen and helium gasses, the temperature and pressure at the core are extreme.
text1_091: Anomalously close to its parent star, this gas giant probably formed in the outer system and later migrated inward due to a chance encounter with some rogue cosmic mass. Primarily composed of hydrogen and helium gasses, the temperature and pressure at the core are extreme.

text2: {卢德教会}的圣地与经济中心。作为{EosExodus}星系中人口最为稠密的行星。{Tartessus}把繁荣的国际大都市矗立于平静而温暖的海洋之上。这个世界的人口由卢德各个派别的信徒组成，而经济则通过出口农作物与手工艺术品为主。在这里，虔诚的农夫与令人尊敬的艺术家不仅随处可见，且大多都过上了平凡而充实的生活。
notes: 这是一个古老而干燥的世界,高度侵蚀的山脉和淤积的浅海遍布于行星表面尽管空气中的含水量要远低于人类所需标准，但因没有活跃的地壳运动，且致命的恒星辐射也在大气与磁场的保护下被阻拦在外，所以该宜居行星被发现后不久，不仅经历了一场大规模殖民化热潮，且随着丰富的矿产资源被陆续发现，就再也无法阻止其贪婪的工业化进程。
text1_095: Seat of the local branch of the Luddic Church and economic center of the system. The quiet cosmopolitan centers of Tartessus housing the Eos Exodus Curia are clustered around calm, warm seas. The world's population is dominated by Luddic practitioners of various sects and, while large, is mostly rural and agrarian, eking out a generally devout existence through subsistence farming and export of handcrafts.
text3_095: An old, dry world that has a much smaller percentage of water in its atmosphere than terran standard. No active plate tectonics; highly eroded mountains and silted shallow seas. The atmosphere and magnetic field protect the surface from stellar radiation. The most accessible mineral resources were mined in a flurry of rapacious industrialism shortly after discovery.
text1_091: Seat of the local branch of the Luddic Church and economic center of the system. text2: 来自外星系的一颗矮行星，当经过{Tartessus}L4}附近时因受到巨大引力而被捕获，千疮百孔的地表不仅丑陋不堪，还把内部所剩不多的气云蒸发一空尽管最近一群流放而来的无神论者与反对派在该行星的废弃设施上建立了一处全新据点，不过这里实际上还是由卢德骑士团所掌控，并从这儿不景气的商业活动中收取少量税款。
text1_095: A dwarf-planet from the outer system captured in the L4 of Tartessus, clouds of volatiles evaporate from the battered surface of this world. The stellar wind weathered infrastructure left from the initial colonization of the system has been re-settled by a lively population of out-of-system nonbelievers and dissidents exiled from Tartessus. The spaceport itself operates under a military administration sponsored by the Knights of Ludd, who collect tithes from commercial activity.
text1_091: A dwarf-planet from the outer system captured in the L4 of Tartessus, clouds of volatiles evaporate from the battered surface of this world. The stellar wind weathered infrastructure left from the initial colonization of the system has been re-settled by a lively population of out-of-system nonbelievers and dissidents exiled from Tartessus. text2: 以前这里是{速子科技}公司经营的研究基地，但随着一场大规模泄露事故，使一种高度活性、并能在星球表面自我维持的未知物质被释放了出来，而难以置信的高温仅在很短的时间内就将附近的一切吞噬一空，甚至是地壳也难逃被融化的命运，而这些深坑至今仍然不时的喷出带有放射性物质的未知气体。在遭到遗弃后，该卫星现在也仅仅是作为卢德骑士团巡逻时的一个临时停靠点。
text1_095: Site of a former research base operated by the Tri-Tachyon Corporation, a massive containment failure released a highly energetic and seemingly self-sustaining process or object which melted into the crust leaving a plume of strange radiation which spews exotic particles to this day. The moon is abandoned of all human activity but for a network of orbiting hazard beacons maintained by the Knights of Ludd.

text2: 在{卢德教会}正式接管{EosExodus}星系的过程中，这颗拥有稀薄大气但异常寒冷的冰冻行星就已经暂停了地球化改造。如今，这里只剩下一些苦修士与坚持教统的骑士们。尽管允许开采数量不多的有机矿物，但只有忠诚的卢德信徒才会被授予开采合同。与{Ceyx}相同，这里都交给了{Orbis}神父来管理。
notes: 修道院坐落于险峻的裂谷与火山岩层的岬角间，而四周都是一些突破冰层包裹的岩体。这里严禁任何外来者随意踏入，特别是那些未获得骑士赫免的不忠者。不过长期不成文的限制贸易往来，随着执政长老{Orbis}神父签署一份自由贸易协定而被打破，不久后这里的浮冰上建立起了一处经济特区，每一天，这而都会发射民用着陆信标来招呼愿意来此贸易的外来者
text1_095: An ice-world with a thin, cold atmosphere, industrial terraforming of the planet was halted around the time of the Luddic takeover of the Eos Exodus system. Virtue may be found in hardship and the Knights embrace this hardship in the martial monastic communities scattered on the surface of Hesperus. Limited organics mining is permitted with contracts awarded exclusively to the Faithful. The administration of Ceyx and Hesperus is shared in the office of a single Presbyter Orbis.
text3_095: Monasteries cling to particularly sublime rifts and promontories of volcanic shields and the occasional pluton that's forced its way through the world-wrapping crust of ice. These forbid outside visitors - particularly the unfaithful - without dispensation from the Knights. However, by authority of the reigning Presbyter Orbis, a number of special economic zones built on the shifting ice floes transmit civilian landing beacons to call outside traders to port.

text2: 因重力而被捕获的矮行星，也是{EosExodus}星系中拥有最大军事设施的地方。为了把这建设成卢德舰队的总部，卢德骑士团在这斥巨资兴建了大量的地下造船厂、军械库、兵营、训练营等设施。与附近的{Hesperus}相同，这里都交给了{Orbis}神父来管理。
text1_095: A captured dwarf planet which holds the largest concentration of military facilities in the Eos Exodus system. The Knights have appropriated and extended vast subsurface ship facilities, armories, barracks, and all the training, administration, and housing facilities one would expect of the home of the Luddic Armada. The administration of Ceyx and Hesperus is shared in the office of a single Presbyter Orbis.
text1_091: A captured dwarf planet which holds the largest concentration of military facilities in the Eos Exodus system. The Knights have appropriated and extended vast subsurface ship facilities, armories, barracks, and all the training, administration, and housing facilities one would expect of the home of the Luddic Armada. text2: 在{Magec}近轨道上的一颗气态巨行星，主要以氢、氦两种气体所组成，由于核心内的温度与压力非常之高，使其看起来极不稳定。因过于靠近{Magec，导致{Chaxiraxi}的表面不断被加热，并使外层不断飘逸出电离离子和气云，而部署在近地轨道上的气体撇渣器就能偶尔收集到这些轻质的挥发物
text1_095: A hot gas giant world in close orbit of Magec; composed mostly of hydrogen and helium gases, the temperature and pressure at the core are extreme. Due to proximity to its primary, the outer layers of Chaxiraxi are continually heated and stripped away in long plumes of shimmering ionized particles. Gas-skimmers occasionally deploy the airy wings of magfield collectors to harvest these light volatiles.

text2: Once a major hub of harvesting operations in the Disk, the station was swarmed by refugees from the Maxios collapse and this hub of processing facilities was turned into a civilian habitat. Through desperate tenacity and hard-earned know-how, the refugees built not only a new civil society but an orbital works supporting scattered asteroid mines and independent surveyors. Nova Maxios is protected by a militia-navy and considers itself the successor polity of the Maxios Charter, but is too small to force major factions to recognize its claim.

Through desperate tenacity and hard-earned know-how, the refugees built not only a new civil society but an orbital works supporting scattered asteroid mines and independent surveyors. Nova Maxios is protected by a militia-navy and considers itself the successor polity of the Maxios Charter, but is too small to force major factions to recognize its claim.
text1_091: Once a major hub of harvesting operations in the Disk, the station was swarmed by refugees from the Maxios collapse and this hub of processing facilities was turned into a civilian habitat. Through desperate tenacity and hard-earned know-how, the refugees built not only a new civil society but a light industrial economy fed by scattered space farms and independent harvesters. Nova Maxios is protected by a militia-navy and considers itself the successor polity of the Maxios Charter, but is too small to force major factions to recognize its claim.
text1_091cn: 曾经作为一处资源采集的重要枢纽，但由于{Maxios}的崩溃，使大量难民将这处枢纽中的所有设施变成了难民营。绝望与苦难让{NonaMaxios}的人们不仅建立起新的政权，且大量的空间农场与独立采矿场等轻工业给这里带来了可观的经济效益。尽管拥有自发组织的民兵海军舰队所保护，但因规模太小难以迫使其它势力承认他们是旧{Maxios}的继任者。

text2: 这里是赏金猎人与海盗们的天堂，几十年前，速子科技}派遣了一支由特遣队与雇佣军所组成的舰队占据了这里，之后不仅建立起了一处大型的交易中心与货运港口，并赶走了所有拒绝支付新租金的家伙。如今这里基本由退休海盗激进分子以及难民所组成，据传言称：任何被运往这儿的货物都会被擦去{ID}并重新标记。除此之外，'Level25'}也是一处在当地享有盛誉的鸡尾酒酒吧
text1_095: A center of mercenary recruitment and a commercial interface with unsavory elements. A Tri-Tachyon task force took over the station some decades ago with a (possibly) valid deed and mercenary fleet. A trading post and port were established and those who refused to pay the new rents evicted. Populated mostly by retired pirates, radicals, and refugees, it is rumored that cargo containers have their IDs wiped and re-tagged here. The cocktail bar "Level 25" enjoys a reputation for having the best drinks in the local volume.

text2: An asteroid habitat was taken by force during the Maxios Charter collapse by a wildly ambitious logistics security officer, Kanta, who cut herself a deal with local pirate groups to act as their secure base of operations. The station is protected by a cloud of stealth-mines and crude firebases while Kanta herself, now nearly two hundred years old, heads a minor dynasty, still holding tight personal control over ‘the family business’.

text1_091cn: 在{Maxios}崩溃后不久，一名野心勃勃的后勤官{Kanta}与当地海盗集团达成协议，并以武力霸占了该空间站，以将其作为他们的安全基地。如今，这处被大量隐形空雷保护的小王朝，依旧被近{200}岁的'女王'{Kanta}所牢牢掌控。

text2: 包含有造船厂、栖息地、工厂、战略储备的轨道空间站。该平台能让人类向已知空间投射军事与工业力量。
text1_095: An enormous spacestation which can host shipyards, habitats, factories, or large stockpiles of weapons and supplies. These platforms allow humanity to project military and industrial power throughout known space.
text1_091: An enormous spacestation which can host shipyards, habitats, factories, or large stockpiles of weapons and supplies. These platforms allow humanity to project military and industrial power throughout known space.

text2:
The Ko Combine r450 "Shepherd" sets the standard for civilian drone tenders with unmatched reliability, low cost, and internal volume given to crew comfort. A wildly popular combat modification package has been assembled by various survivalist and pirate groups, the "HK" mod, which consists of specifications to up-armour the hull for combat and supercharge factory-spec systems for greater burst speed and weapon function. Even modified, the Shepherd is fragile, so as in civilian life it relies on a swarm of “Borer” utility drones to do its work.

The "Borer" is built on a hardy, maneuverable semi-autonomous drone chassis with shielding suitable for hazardous operations in which high radiation or physical impacts may be expected. Commonly used in mining applications, they have also found use in salvage, ordnance disposal, and even fission meltdown clean-up. The HK mod package gives specifications for altering the primary cutting beam's focus and patches the rudimentary AI with crude tactical algorithms pirated from obsolete Domain Colonial Garrison drone software. Appendices of the mod package recommend caution when employing HK-modified drones in non-combat situations.

text1_091cn:
Ko联合实业}的著名公关代表曾经将{R450}牧羊人评价成民用护卫舰的典范之作，使得这艘拥有可靠性能,低成本以及舒适乘坐空间的护卫舰风靡一时。而之后一种专为牧羊人-级设计且广受欢迎的战斗模组，被生存主义者或海盗团伙组装到了船上，这种名为{'HK'}的模组不仅提供了可靠的额外装甲，且加装的推进装置也能使该舰获得暂时的速度与机动性的提升。可即使经过改装，该舰依然非常脆弱，因此在作为民用舰船的日子里，它一般依靠实用的螟蜂无人机来代替其完成工作。

螟蜂无人机是基于结实且易操作的半自动无人机的基础框架上改进而成，尽管缺乏护盾，但仍能在高辐射的危险环境下进行工作，且经常用作于采矿作业、打捞、排爆、甚至是清理核心熔毁。其{HK}模组不仅提高了切割激光器的聚焦程度，还用仿自于人之领殖民地驻军的无人机战术软件将其基础人工智能进行升级。要注意的是，这种模组的附件特别标注了{[严禁在非战斗中使用带有HK模组的无人机，否则后果自负]

text2: 银河救赎教会的正式成立，是受到人之领星门崩溃时一位名为'卢德'人士做出的殉道行为而获得的启发，以亚伯拉罕契约与一些来源可疑的人之领反对腐败、堕落、享乐主义和超人类事物的著作为主要核心，而建立起的一种等级体系分明、教条高度融合的教会组织。教会不仅向信徒们描绘了一幅更简单的生活方式、即人人拥有美德、人力资源充足的美好蓝图，并反对自星门崩溃以来那些企图分裂整片星域的暴力行径与科技差异。
text1_095: Inspired by the martyrdom of a figure known as 'Ludd' during the fall of the Domain, the Church of Galactic Redemption is a hierarchical church with highly syncretic dogma formed from a core of Abrahamic texts and apocrypha along with Domain-era reaction against perceived corruption, depravity, hedonism, and transhuman abomination. The Church offers a vision of life lived more simply, of agrarian virtue and humanistic values and prayer against the violence and technological alienation that's torn the Sector apart in the years since the Fall.

The Church offers a vision of life lived more simply, of agrarian virtue and humanistic values and prayer against the violence and technological alienation that's torn the Sector apart in the years since the Fall.

text2: 卢德银河救赎教会是仿照千年前的修道士团体而建立的军事部门。在教会管控的区域里，他们被授权去执行'绝对正确之事'，以及通过武力来保证一个事实——美德将得到促进，恶行将得到严惩。即使在教会控制区域之外的地方，当时机允许，他们也将在暗中用同样的方式来履行他们的职责。
text1_095: The military branch of Luddic Church of Galactic Redemption, modeled on monastic warrior societies from previous millennia. In areas of Church domination they are authorized to enforce Technological Correctness as well as ensuring, through force, that virtue is promoted and vice chastised. In areas outside Church domination, when able, they covertly impose the same.
text1_091: The military branch of Luddic Church of Galactic Redemption, modeled on monastic warrior societies from previous millennia. In areas of Church domination they are authorized to enforce Technological Correctness as well as ensuring, through force, that virtue is promoted and vice chastised. In areas outside Church domination, when able, they covertly impose the same.

text2: 卢德左径}是一种松散的团体，其成员是一群被边缘化的、激进的世界末日教派分子，这些世界末日卢德主义者们声称：他们对卢德给予人们的信息有着更为深刻的解读。在他们眼中，教会是妥协且腐败的，因为他们在世界末日临近之时,把世俗的自我安慰放在了追求真正的救赎道路之前。末日决战就是{"现在"！其帷幕已经拉开！——}只有通过强有力的正义行为，才能更大程度地击溃恶魔，只有通过暴力才能清扫人类对神的傲慢与不敬。在他们如此宣称之际，卢德左径}必然意识到他们已经陷入几乎与星域所有势力为敌的困境。
text1_095: The Luddic Path is a loosely associated category of radical, decentralized, apocalyptic sects of Luddism that claim a truer interpretation of Ludd's Message. They view the Church as compromised and corrupt, putting worldly ego and comforts before the True Luddic Path in these, the end-times. The war of Armageddon is NOW and the lines are drawn! Only through forceful righteous action shall Good destroy Evil, and only through violence will the abomination of humanity's hubris and rebellion against God be swept aside in a final act of redemption. Or so they claim. The Luddic Path necessarily finds itself at odds with nearly all other factions in the Sector.

text2: 严格来说，海盗比起一个统一的势力，更像是一种松散的联合体。他们之中有土匪、强盗、逃兵、掠夺者、赏金猎人,雇佣兵、和一些与星域中的强大势力们一样拥有着强烈斗争心并好战的舰长们。许多海盗因受到压迫逃离了星域的主流社会，并在远离核心世界的地方藏匿。大部分海盗舰长几乎不称呼自己为海盗，而是把自己看做反对{霸主}或{英仙座联盟}立下的不适当规则的挑战者，为这个已陷入歧途的社会所犯下的错误而向他们复仇。并凭借自己的聪明才智,带走一切能带走的东西。这些舰长的特点很明显，他们对自由和荣誉有着极为深切的渴望。通常情况下,他们不怎么为难那些带着官方身份识别器的同行们，并对他们保留有极大的宽容。
text1_095: Not technically a unified faction but more a loose category of bandits, brigands, deserters, looters, soldiers of fortune, mercenaries, and free captains that share a common belligerence with the established powers of the Sector. Many pirates are runaways from the mainstream Sector society - usually oppressed by the status quo, stowaways from core worlds. Most pirate captains would hardly call themselves such, rather seeing themselves as challengers to the inept rule of the Hegemony or the League, seeking vengeance for the wrongs caused by such a misled society and taking what they can take through their cleverness and audacity. These captains can be characterized by their insatiable thirst for freedom and glory. Naturally, they give little thought to those that carry an official identification beacon, reserving their magnanimity for their fellow-travelers - other pirates.

text2: {辛达强权}是一个最近因{霸主}军事介入{Andrada}星系而产生的政治团体。那次军事干预由前{霸主}海军上将{PhilipAndrada}所领导。这名在{霸主}海军心理档案被描述成'机智而富有领导力，但有些过于自恋'的人，成为了如今{辛达强权}的实际掌权人。按照他的说法，辛达强权}是在{Andrada}危机中经历磨练，由新一代人民所建立。这些人不仅拥有英勇的精神和清晰的目标，且怀揣着更为强大的信念与决心，足以克服分歧或分裂并战胜那个在星门崩溃后的考验中，渺小的且只会带来混乱的议会政府。然而整个星域的人们认为：他们撑死也不过是个想在乱世获取利益的军事独裁政体。
text1_095: The Sindrian Diktat is a polity founded in a relatively recent Hegemony military intervention in the Askonia system led by Admiral Philip Andrada, formerly of the Hegemony Navy. Andrada's Hegemony psych profile describes him as "intelligent, charismatic, yet prone to narcissistic excess". In his words, the Diktat was "formed in the crucible of the Askonia Crisis and with it a new people: a race of humans with emboldened spirit and clarity of purpose; stronger, possessing the will and determination to overcome the divisions and petty parliamentary politics that bred only chaos when tested by the collapse of the Gate System." Considered by the Sector at large to be a military dictatorship.

text2: Asharu}地球化改造项目中一处被遗弃的轨道空间站。没人期望能在这找到任何有价值的东西。除了废弃折断的残骸，这里只剩下一些空置的机库、被焊接在一起的废弃货舰、蜂窝状的破损燃料罐，而这里也一度成为了工程师与难民的聚集地。所幸的是，部分被动式能量收集器与三级生命维持模块的正常运作，使这处残破不堪的空间站依旧能在轨道上勉强运行。
text1_095: An abandoned orbital staging area for the Asharu terraforming project. Castoff bulk-carrier segments welded between a honeycomb of emptied fuel tanks once formed concourses teeming with engineers and colonists. The hangars stand empty but for a few slumped, stripped hulks. Passive energy collectors and tertiary life-support modules keep the station functioning and in orbit, barely. No one would expect to find anything of value here.
text1_091: An abandoned orbital staging area for the Asharu terraforming project. Castoff bulk-carrier segments welded between a honeycomb of emptied fuel tanks once formed concourses teeming with engineers and colonists. The hangars stand empty but for a few slumped, stripped hulks. Passive energy collectors and tertiary life-support modules keep the station functioning and in orbit, barely. No one would expect to find anything of value here.
text1_091cn: Asharu}地球化改造项目中一处被遗弃的轨道空间站。没人期望能在这找到任何有价值的东西。除了废弃折断的残骸，这里只剩下一些空置的机库、被焊接在一起的废弃货舰、蜂窝状的破损燃料罐，而这里也一度成为了工程师与难民的聚集地。所幸的是，部分被动式能量收集器与三级生命维持模块的正常运作，使这处残破不堪的空间站依旧能在轨道上勉强运行。

text2: '冒险家'、海盗、雇佣兵以及人渣恶棍聚集的海盗基地。这处隐藏在势力领域之间的小型前哨站，尽管没有法律的约束，但却由一个不成文的规矩来维持脆弱的和平，因此很多商人或走私者也愿意在这进行信息交易，并出售一些非法所得的赃物。
text1_095: A pirate base where "adventurers", freebooters, mercenaries and other such scum and villainy gather. Usually a small outpost hiding in the dark places between the spheres of major factions' interest. Here there are no laws, but an unwritten code of bravado and posturing maintains a tense peace so deals can be made, information traded, and spoils sold to unscrupulous traders.

text2: 点缀在行星表面上的冰火山使地壳被厚厚的冰幔所覆盖。除了一些冰冻的废土被大型龙门架运走，以等待重新回收利用，且这里可供开采的挥发性物质也被大量提取，以用于满足这个星系其它区域的地球化改造工程。在这里，氨冰冰川夹缝间的老旧设施不仅随处可见，且被大量分散的独立矿工所利用，并过着难以想象的艰苦生活。
text1_095: The thick, icy crust of this world is fed by cryovolcanoes that dot the surface. These frozen wastes are scored by mass-driver gantries from a time when the volatile elements of this world were extracted on a massive scale to feed terraforming efforts elsewhere in-system. Some of the old equipment has been appropriated by scattered bands of independent miners who scratch out a meagre living between the glaciers of ammonia-ice.

text2: Originally built by Eridani-Utopia to coordinate volatiles extraction for massive terraforming projects, the station has been taken over by ‘adventurers’, freebooters, mercenaries seeking to avoid the watchful eye and heavy hand of the Hegemony. Here there are no laws, but an unwritten code of bravado and posturing maintains a tense peace so deals can be made, information traded, and spoils sold. Independent miners who work the moons of Barad gather here to sell their hauls, trade tall tales, and otherwise unwind.

text1_091cn: 最初由{天苑四-乌托邦改造集团}建造，目的是为了在大规模土地改造中协调挥发物的提取工作。如今这已被一群冒险家、强盗以及雇佣军所占领,以试图躲避{霸主}对他们的监视与施压。这儿没有法律，只有不成文的规矩维持着当地的和平，因此任何人都可以来此进行贸易、交换信息以及出售战利品，而在{Barad}卫星上工作过的矿工们也聚集于此，出售一些带来的货物、诉说着夸张的故事、或进行其他的放松活动。

text2: Achaman}空间站的意义在于，可以让{Guayota}的各种居民不必冒着被海盗抢劫的风险，就能在这处相对较安全的港口内进行商业活动。而作为'看守人'的{速子科技}也很乐意利用该空间站的价值来获利，正如人们所常说的：所有东西都能在{Achaman}空间站里被卖掉。
text1_095: The value of Achaman Station is as a relatively safe port of call for the various inhabitants of Guayota's Disk to interact with traders from the Sector at-large, who otherwise rarely risk the pirates and difficult navigation of the Disk. The Tri-Tachyon Corporation, as 'caretaker' of the station, is well-situated to exploit its value handily - and do. It is often said that everything is for sale at Achaman Station.

text2:
The Hegemony is a martial successor state to the Domain formed by a ‘lost legion’ trapped in a backwater system by the collapse of the Domain gate network. Built upon a creative interpretation of protocols which indefinitely extends Domain-style martial law, the founders of the Hegemony believed that the overriding cause of restoring the Domain and therefore stability, peace, and prosperity to the Sector and indeed the entire galaxy must come before certain niceties of human rights. The survival of humanity is at stake and it is only the discipline of the Hegemony military that protects worlds where some semblance of the normalcy of human civilization can be nurtured. Anything that threatens the Great Cause must be neutralized; if a few activists must be discouraged for the greater good, so be it.

Civilian hierarchies exist to govern the planets and stations under Hegemony rule but are entirely subordinate to the military. The specifics of civilian organization varies between worlds, as was Domain policy. When in doubt, the Hegemony applies a modified Domain-era colonial charter to dictate political organization. This standard-charter civilian hierarchy is generally elected, however as per martial law valid candidates must be approved by the local military authority. Exceptional times require exceptional measures, yet still the Hegemony fosters the flickering flame of galactic democracy under the same principles that founded the Domain.

text1_091cn:
作为{人之领}的军事继承国，霸主}最初是由一支因{人之领}星门系统崩溃后被困在一个偏远星系的迷失军团所组建。它的建国宣言基于一个能'创造性地'将{人之领}时期的军事戒严法进行无限期延长的解释条款。霸主}的建立者们坚信：想要重新回归{人之领}的体制，维持全星区甚至整个银河系的和平、稳定以及繁荣，就必须凌驾于琐碎的人权之上。人类正经历生死存亡的紧要关头，只有处于{霸主}严格的军事体制下才能保护那些可以孕育基本正常人类文明的世界。任何危及这项'伟业'的隐患都必须遭到排除；如果一些激进分子因无知或利益而极力阻止这份伟业，那么将其作为牺牲品也在所不辞。

在{霸主}所统治的行星和空间站里，便于治理用的民间政体依然存在，但却完全隶属于军队。因{人之领}的政策原因,导致民间组织的细节在不同世界中各不相同。一旦这些组织存在问题，霸主}就会用个修订后的{人之领}时期的殖民章程来强行决定政府结构。尽管标准民间政体是由民选产生，但根据军事戒严法，有效的候选必须得到当地军事机关的核准。虽然特殊时期需采取特殊措施，但{霸主}仍在{人之领}所建立的原则下，抚育着银河民主那在风中摇曳的火焰。

text2:
The most powerful megacorporation in the Sector after the fall of the Domain gate system, Tri-Tachyon specialized in cutting-edge AI development (including several notable cases of violating the Domain ban on autonomous alpha+ level AI) and exotic high-power devices (starship engines and warp drives, power generators, energy converters, forcefields). Since the Collapse, Tri-Tachyon has vastly diversified its operations and insinuated itself throughout the Sector. Even hostile factions, paranoid of hardwired backdoors, find themselves forced to employ standard Tri-Tachyon devices, beginning with the ubiquitous Tri-Tachyon PDA.

From a certain perspective, the Tri-Tachyon corporate charter’s peculiar algorithmic self-modifying features might be considered to be an abstract form of AI which makes use of human corporate officers as integral components, though this is a philosophical argument which was never satisfactorily resolved in a way that led to any additional convictions of violating the Domain’s AI ban.

text1_091cn:
速子科技}是在{人之领}星门系统崩溃后，星域中最为强大的大型企业。它专注于尖端{AI}科技的开发，并多次违反{人之领}禁止研究阿尔法级以上的自主行动{AI}的禁令。和研究一些外来的高能设备，如星舰发动机、曲速引擎、能量发生器、能量转换器、力场装置等。自星门崩溃以来，速子科技}极大地扩展了它的运营方式并成功将自己烙印在了整个星域的运作之中。甚至它的敌对势力，或是那些执意要在自己系统里留下固线后门的偏执狂们，最终也不得不开始采购并使用一些{速子科技}的标准设备，并直面那些他们恨之入骨却又无所不在的{速子科技}个人终端。

从某种角度来说，速子科技}的公司章程所拥有的特殊算法以及自调整特征也许可被当成是让人类公司员工代替{AI}作为完整部分以构成抽象的AI组织。然而这依旧是一个无法解决的哲学问题，因为现在还没有任何令人满意的方法能避免在这个过程中因违背{人之领}的{AI}禁令而获得定罪。

text2:
An alliance formed to counter Hegemony domination of the Sector. Members of the League don’t necessarily agree on all issues, domestic or otherwise, and may even come into armed conflict with one another. But the League is united when it comes to the Hegemony who they consider to be illegitimately enforcing martial law in the name of the Domain, a dead political entity. The League, by its laws, unites against other external threats such as particularly meddlesome megacorporations, warlords, and the Luddic Path. 

The Persean League is not intrinsically egalitarian or for individual freedom as-such – the purpose of the League is freedom of the constituent polities with any matters of internal politics of those polities to be left to their own devices. While the Domain might have intervened against the domestic policies of the worlds it ruled, the League specifically forbids such intervention.
text3: 甚至为此爆发过激烈的武装冲突，可当他们直面{霸主}这个被看作是以{人之领}名义非法推行军事戒严法的呆板政体时，他们的意志是无比统一的。联盟将遵循自己的法律以及准则，联合起来对抗那些来自外部的威胁，尤其是一些好事的大型集团、军阀，和{卢德左径}。

text1_091cn:
英仙座联盟}是一个把反抗{霸主}对星域的完全统治而作目的建立的同盟体。尽管联盟成员对于国内外事务难以达成共识，甚至为此爆发过激烈的武装冲突，可当他们直面{霸主}这个被看作是以{人之领}名义非法推行军事戒严法的呆板政体时，他们的意志是无比统一的。联盟将遵循自己的法律以及准则，联合起来对抗那些来自外部的威胁，尤其是一些好事的大型集团、军阀，和{卢德左径。

英仙座联盟}并不主张真正意义上的人人平等或绝对的个体自由。联盟的目标是实现让任何政府的内部政治问题留给他们自己来着手解决。尽管{人之领}的法律有时会干预他们所统治世界的内政，但联盟的特令已经明确禁止了这种干预。

text2: 比起一个统一的势力，自由联盟}更像是由一些松散的政体和那些缺乏与其他主流势力合作，且不具备共有特质的自由主义者所组成的联合体。在{自由联盟}的世界里，那些将其看做家的飞行员们经常分享一些有价值的数据信息，以大方慷慨的价格互相交易物资，并愿意更好地保护这个他们共同维持的自由而去合作一些短期安全措施和军事行动。然而也有这么一种情况，当相互间的信任土崩瓦解，自由联盟}的成员不仅会因无端的猜疑而拒绝支持其他同僚，并展开恶意竞争，且对他们同胞发生的所有不幸而视若无睹。
text1_095: Not a unified faction as such, the Independents are a loose category of polities and free agents unified more by a lack of association with a major faction than any shared qualities. Independent worlds and the spacers who call them home often share reputation data, trade generously among themselves, and will readily cooperate to perform short-term security and military actions to better protect what freedom they have maintained by working together. Equally likely, trust can break down, and Independents will suspiciously deny each other favors, compete viciously, and turn a blind eye to the misfortune of neighbours.

text2: Chicomoztoc}作为该星系首批殖民对象的行星之一。由于被选作成为一处重要的工业枢纽，因此一片规模宏大的纳米工厂群就坐落于此。这颗略适合地球化的候补行星，因早期无节制的工业发展以及受到后期战争的波及，使其原本就稀薄的大气充满了复杂的硫化合物、有机精炼副产品以及令人担忧但可控的锕系有毒粉尘。
notes: Chicomoztoc}庞大的人口都定居于由强大的政治煽动家们控制的地下建筑群中，他们不仅向失业者许诺改革和岗位，并筹集了大量的竞争性技术，甚至还收取贿赂为罪犯提供庇护伞，以便为他们自己的联盟服务。建筑群有时会因为骚乱、抗议和暴动而紧急封锁，但只要工厂群安好，并制造出足够的货物、机械、工具和船体，霸主}便只会对这儿睁只眼闭只眼。
text1_095: One of the first planets targeted for colonization in the Sector, Chicomoztoc was selected to become a center of industry, host to a nexus of huge nanoforges. Only a marginal terraforming candidate upon discovery, rapid early industry and later war has left the atmosphere choked with complex sulphur compounds, organics refining by-products, and a concerning but manageable dusting of actinides.
text3_095: The enormous population of Chicomoztoc lives in underground arcologies ruled in turn by powerful demagogues - promising reform and jobs for the masses of unemployed - or members of the numerous competing technocrat/criminal patronage networks serving their home hive-coalition or, as often, whoever has bought them off. Hives are occasionally locked down by riots, protest, and insurrection but so long as the Forges are kept safe and churning out mountains of goods, machinines, tools, and starship hulls, the Hegemony overlords meddle little in domestic affairs.
text1_091: One of the first planets targeted for colonization in the Sector, Chicomoztoc was selected to become a center of industry, host to a nexus of huge nanoforges. Only a marginal terraforming candidate upon discovery, rapid early industry and later war has left the atmosphere choked with complex sulphur compounds, organics refining by-products, and a concerning but manageable dusting of actinides.
